title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: An excellent course. Very much appreciated the simple to install and use Eclipse environment and sbt tool. The classes were very clear and the exercises extremely well described. I struggled on this course, Functional Programming is quite a paradigm shift for me - really glad I made the effort. Looking forward to a future course from Dr Odersky.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: This course was well designed. The assignment submission tool able to give feedback and pointed out which area I lost point. This was probably the hardest course I've ever taken, provided that it was my first attempt learning functional programming. Nevertheless, it was worth it.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: The best class I have taken on programming. This course does demand a lot of work from you but it opens up you to new way to think about programming. I had significant professional development experience in Java, but that didn't make it any easier.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Great course. Everything was on time, lectures were great. Problem sets were insightful. Definitely recommend. It is a functional programming language course though, so be prepared for lots of recursion.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents:
Excellent course for Java developers that want to try something functional.

Also this course doesn't require experience with Java, but it will a big plus.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Definitely one of the best programming courses I have ever had. It has a great structure and comes with really interesting and challenging assignments.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Very well presented and well designed assignment to help in learning. Come with a fresh mind and will learn a lot of new things

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Great course. A bit complicated specially the last two weeks, but not imposible at all. I've learned a lot with this course.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Really great course. A very good way to know the concepts of functional programming and to catch its beauty.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Excellent introduction to both functional programming and Scala. Well defined assignments and coherent lectures.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Great learning. Non-trivial concepts are explained in a clear way. I could not wait for the next week exercise...

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Fantastic course. Martin Odesky is a great educator. I now really love scala.

title: Functional Programming Principles in Scala
review_contents: Great course, everything put well together, cool assignments.

title: Introduction to Sustainability
review_contents: Complex subjects such as Malthusian thinking, Tragedy of the Commons, Milankovitch cycles, climate vs. weather, greenhouse gases, and many others were very well explained by Prof. Tomkin. Now I'm able to understand sustainability discussions as well as possible ways of keeping our planet healthy.

title: Introduction to Sustainability
review_contents: Very interesting! Course was well-setup. I was a bit reluctant to participate in the discussion forums at first (as this was my first MOOC), but once I did I learned a lot from it.

title: Introduction to Sustainability
review_contents: A great course, very well organised. Highly recommended. Quite a bit of work, I spent around 9 hours per week on it. Feel like I have earned my certificate.

review_contents: Boring and outdated lectures. Def not the right way to learn Android app development. I'd recommend serious learners to directly start by following the training material on the official Android documentation site: developer.android.com/training . If you prefer video lectures then the Udacity courses listed in their Nanodegree curriculum are the best. They are co-produced by Google engineers.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: I used to struggle a lot in learning Android before I took these courses. Prof. A. Porter explains everything clearly and the studying facilities provided by Coursera platform such as discussion forums and peer assessments makes the learning process much easier. Moreover, the course material gets updated in respect to Android Studio, Eclipse and the latest APIs when necessary.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: This course makes learning to program Android apps easy and funny. I would definitely recommend to anyone who has absolutely no background on mobile development (as me) and wants to start quickly but on solid knowledge. It¡¯s a super course and Pr Porter excels at explaining all the concepts.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: The technology used was outdated. No android studio and it was hard to follow because of this. I think the professor knows what he's talking about, but needs to update his videos to make thing up-to-date.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: Thanks Mr. Porter. It is the best course ever. The explanations were crystal clear and I have learned a lot here.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: I had programmed before with Android. But in this class I learned that I did not know the fundamentals about Android. This first part of the course has complimented my knowledge about Android. I will continue studying the remains of the courses, of course.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: Excellent course!! These courses gave me a great revision, corrected some of my concepts, and taught me a lot more new materials. I recommend this course to those who want to challenge themselves. Thanks Prof Porter and team.

review_contents:
I had a hard time following the course, it takes a lot of time.

In the end it looks that I didn't learn a lot :(

Let's go to the second part and hope that more ground is achieved.

title: Programming Mobile Applications for Android Handheld Systems: Part 1
review_contents: The course was really helpful, it introduced me to the Android world like no other course did in the past. I will do the whole Specialization as the other courses seem to be great too.

The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: The whole "course" is doable in about 2 hours. It's laughably easy ? the main point is to get you to install RStudio. Granted, if you've never used Github it'll be a bit bewildering, but I think it's wildly excessive to have a Signature Track certificate with a $49 fee to basically prove you're capable of signing up to a website.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: The course is very easy, and its material is very shallow, it should have been only a first-week introduction to another course in Coursera's Data specialization track.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents:
If you have never worked with Git, GitHub, R, or RStudio, this is a great (very short) introduction.

I have seen a lot of people in later courses of the specialization complain that they did not know how to upload the peer projects onto github, so I would say it can be a very useful class.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Very difficult if you don't have any prior programming and computer science knowledge. This is not a beginners course. Frustrating, challenging, assumes students have enough prior knowledge to fill in the gaps during the lectures. As someone with no prior computer experience of any kind (other than basic Word) I was lost almost immediately.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Taking this course was very annoying due to it's lack of structure(specifically when the quizzes should be taken) & shallow content (mostly overviews). Also if you have an older computer installing to software needed to complete the class maybe a challenge. I may try it again when I need a new computer.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Overall, the class is pretty simple, and far easier than the other classes in this specialization. Really, the hardest part of this course was finding the complete instructions for the final project. The first part was found easily enough, but the other parts of the project are not obvious.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: The course was a good introduction. As an experienced programmer, I found the course quite easy. However, I do appreciate the focus on setting up the tools and environment. Too many people leave version control to chance. It is something people are just supposed to pick up as they go along.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Eh. I wasn't really impressed with the presentation. It's too low a level if you've had any experience at all and it isn't a particularly good explanation if you've never seen this stuff before. I will try the R class at this point but I am already shopping around for alternatives.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: When you spend your time every week, submit the weekly quizzes and the final project this course is worthwile as a start of the Data Scientist specialization. I enjoyed it.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Very easy course. Just set up your github account, and you are done! This course could have been combined with other courses.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: This course is fairly weak. It might be interesting if you really have no idea about Data Science, but if you have any knowledge you might find far too obvious.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents:
The course was as expected, given its description in Coursera.

I found the exercises very easy. I don't think it makes sense to enroll unless you're aiming at the data science specialization.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: This course provides a catalog of tools for subsequent courses in this set (eg: GitHub, RStudio, etc). Its a pretty decent introduction even if you want to get stared with R programming.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: What a deception, just a couple of exercises on Github. Why do they make us pay for this? A very bad introduction to the "Data Science" specialization.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: The course was fine -- it was really an intro in the sense of just having you set up accounts and various software. The bulk of the time is spent listening to the lectures. It probably isn't a month's worth of material.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Strange class as in there is very little content. Basically, the instructors want you to install GitHub and R Studio and learn a few basic terms and ideas about data science.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: This is a joke, not a course. A way to make money for JHU. Total scam. There's literally about an hour of work in this course.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Teaching was good but too less content for a course. Very basic stuff that one can just read and understand in little time.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: For programmers with even only a little bit of experience this course is a no-brainer. But I agree with other commenters here that if you had no programming background, then this course is a must. It introduces beginners into fundamental concepts such as Version Control and Markdown and prepares for the rest of the specialization.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: This course gives you a great introduction to the overall concepts of data science and the tools that you will need to use in the other courses in the certificate sequence. Given that I have struggled with other stats-related courses on Coursera, I truly appreciated the tutorial style of this first course.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: I've just begun this course so I don't know how much time I will spend each week but it is definitely holding my interest. It is great because it's an entry level course to a complex subject. It has free tools and they instruct you in getting set up.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Learned a bit but overall it is literally not worth the price of admission. I think that this course could be offered for free and maybe the others are worth paying for. Hope that the rest of the specialization is worthwhile

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents:
Well, this course is nice for beginners, specifically those who don¢¥t have a clue about R language.

For those who already knew R and a little bit of github, is just a couple of hours of lectures and that will be it

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: OK Course. What bothered me most was that you do not see the instructor for most of the course. You just see the slides and hear a voice. And one instructor hadn't prepared well so it was awful to listen to.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: The course content is more like a prerequisite for the first week of a real course. There's nothing to it, even if you're a complete beginner, you can complete this in a couple of hours.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: This is really just a primer course for the following courses in the specialization. If you're familiar with R and Git/Github already, you can skip it easy.

title: The Data Scientist¡¯s Toolbox
review_contents: Very basic: its role seems to be simply to prepare the student for other classes in the Data Science specialization.

title: Hardware Security
review_contents: The course is too formal and theoretical. It gathers and tries to systematize academic approaches for Hardware Security that are often very far away from the practice. Quizzes are boring and check your ability to remember definitions or making modular arithmetic. Consider this course as a source of the keywords for the topic but not a foundation of a good understanding.

title: Hardware Security
review_contents: Difficult for anyone who hasn't previously had experience to digital design basics (such as satisfiability don't cares), and truth tables. The professor gives a good introduction to the topics, but I believe that my previous work in the area helped immensely

title: Hardware Security
review_contents: The course is not self-contained as claimed. The professor doesn't do a good job in explaining the topics, and it all seems to theoretical. Not recommended.

title: Statistical Inference
review_contents: Not recommended - take Duke University's course instead. Confusing lectures and poor development of homework material. Peer grading was poor due to lack of clarity in the grading rubric. Appeared to be no interaction by instructor or feedback (vice Duke course in which the instructor was highly engaged). Don't waste your time or money.

title: Statistical Inference
review_contents: To the difference of many I found this course very interesting, difficult for sure and true the lecturer could be fast. You need to spend time with the slides, but if you want to grab inference this is the course. Keep in mind it is a bit as when you are at uni, one hour lesson then 4 hours work.

title: Statistical Inference
review_contents: Pointless - don't waste you time. Especially money. These people plainly cannot teach - but they can take your 49 dollars, they are good at that.

title: Statistical Inference
review_contents: Awful course with really poor lectures - they are confusing even if you know some statistics. The course is not engaging at all and after that I decided not to take any verified courses at all.

title: Statistical Inference
review_contents:
Too much content for a few weeks, if you don¢¥t have a clue about statistics, It will be hard.

Also, the professor isn¢¥t bad, the guy really knows a lot, but the teaching method is not awesome as in the other courses. Maybe a little more didactic (Specially because of the math), would be helpful, more examples and more weeks to cover the whole content.

title: Statistical Inference
review_contents: The material in the class is solid, but is poorly described. These are the foundations of statistical analysis, and unfortunately there's a lot of statistics jargon that students aren't going to be familiar with in here.

title: Energy 101: The Big Picture
review_contents: The course gives some nice facts about Energy production, conversion and use. Would have been nicer if the prof had been less biased towards some of the newer technologies.

title: R Programming
review_contents: Most, if not all, of the videos presented in this course are available on YouTube, and very little additional instruction is provided in the actual Coursera class. You have the option to pay for a verified certificate, but there is no value added for the $$. Better resources are out there.

title: R Programming
review_contents: I'm enjoying the course - but I don't feel that the lectures prepare you in any way to do the programming assignments. Perhaps it would be better if an assignment is posted on a weekly basis and the explanation is given in the following week's lectures. Solutions to the assignments are available on the web, so one could easily complete the course without truly understanding it.

title: R Programming
review_contents: This course is definitely not for someone who does not have programming background or does not have an aptitude toward programming. I have been programming for number of years and I am enjoying learning R. This course will give you a good base and you can built your knowledge upon it. Just remember to do a lot of practice.

title: R Programming
review_contents: Quizzes seem to fit well with the lectures and can be accomplished in the 4-9 hours a week. Week2 (assignment 1) is insanely hard and there seems to be a huge gap of knowledge in how to code in R. I would suggest the course have a "Foundations in R" course for newbies to learn code. Then run the assignments from this course as a "Programming in R" course. The leap is simply huge.

title: R Programming
review_contents: Gives fast pace view of main features of the R language. Not a lot of time was put into creating this class and the materials.

title: R Programming
review_contents: I personally found video lectures to be rather boring and definitely too "academic", in a way. However, programming assignments are exceptionally challenging, involving and they actually force you to learn, understand and create something through R. Very useful and funny experience, really.

title: R Programming
review_contents: I don't recommend this course at all. The lectures present some high level subset of material while the quiz and programming require quite a detailed level of knowledge. The interactive tool "swirl" was decent to learn the basics, but does not prepare one for the complexity of the programming assignments. Teach yourself with other online tutorials and you will be better off.

title: R Programming
review_contents: At my second attempt I have tried the first assignment. Although I have the correct answers I have submitted the script and been told they are incorrect. It will take you longer than 4 weeks

title: R Programming

I spent countless hours searching through stack overflow and the course forum to no avail.

title: R Programming

You can try and solve it on your own if you want to spend that time, but I recommend just getting a book or finding another online course. (e.g. codeschool).

title: R Programming

Would suggest beginners in R to google for wonderful beginner tutorials before attempting these assignments.

title: R Programming

In short if you're new to R don't bother and if you know how to write R fluently than you don't need to take a course.

title: R Programming

review_contents:
Great bite sized "chunks" of material, easy tho follow and understand. Plus I enjoyed the way in which it practised what it preached i.e. review and repetition at regular intervals. I now use Pomodoro at work to ensure I make regular focused progress on a number of competing priorities.

I've completed a few MOOCs but this was by far the easiest/most enjoyable to return to.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I really enjoyed taking this course! I was always unsatisfied with my methods and habits whenever I am trying to learn something new. I would cram the night before a test and end up forgetting everything the day after. I wanted to change these habits. Taking this course has given me a whole new insight to learning. And now, I'm a lot more confident in the way I learn.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Excellent! Great presenters who explained everything in easy to understand (and remember) terms. I did this course to assist me with our child; a struggling learner, to ensure that I teach a good foundation to studying and learning with the latest information and understanding about how the brain works. I have recommended this course to many, just do it!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I cannot express enough how much i learnt from this course. The material, pace, wealth of resources are priceless. Throughout the period of my learning, I couldn't wait for the next day to come to learn more. I am already using many of the techniques and I am going back to my notes almost on daily basis. I am truly grateful for this course, simply beautiful.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: The audio and visual work effectively together to aid in the learning process. The course offers an easy-to-understand review of research to back up the suggestions for better learning techniques. Great blend of theory and hands-on. I started using what I learned from this course with my own students even before completing the course. Mission accomplished!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: So many insightful ways to help you learn anything. The additional videos and extended selection of readings take you even further. I really wish this was required for all junior high or high school students; it would encourage those who don't just 'pick up' new concepts and supply those who do with additional skills for those times when they will be challenged.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This course was very informative. It provides practical tips that you can apply in your own studies to learn more effectively. It has breadth and depth. And I loved the interviews. Because this is a self-paced course, my advice is to take from this course what you believe is most useful and ignore the rest. And then you can always come back to it for more tips.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: One of the best, if not the best MOOCs for learning how to learn stuff, rather than just building up on past knowledge. My first complete course and the results are pretty phenomenal. Would recommend it to anyone who wants to learn stuff, that too in the most efficient way. Complement with Scott Young and you have the ultimate learning machine.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: It's a great course. I'm impressed by the content shared, and just as impressed by the content delivery. It puts in practice the learning principles the course teaches. The intermittent quizzes (both ungraded and graded ones) are very helpful in reinforcing learning - the recall and the testing principle in learning. Thanks lots, Barbara and Terry!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Really worthwhile 4 week course; unlike some other courses, almost every single insight in the course is immediately useable. LHTL is a life skill,; if you think you may have missed out on the skill, do the course. even if you think you area good learner, i would be surprised if you didn't find something in it that wasn't worth the time commitment.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This course was alright. I thought most of the techniques were simply common sense; however, there were some tips I did find useful, which makes the whole class worth it. This shouldn't take you very long and Dr Oakley is wonderful. She seems like the nicest person and I found her to be soothing and was great at explaining the material.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I found the course very interesting and learned quite some new things I did not know. I would suggest to introduce some practice in the program (optional, for reaching the "cum laude" score on the certification for instance) to push students a bit further and ensure certain techniques get grounded in our heads. Thanks a lot for sharing!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I loved this course and think every high school and college kid should take it. Understanding how your brain acquires new information makes it possible to learn more efficiently and shed bad habits that often carry on into adulthood. As the parent of a high schooler, I'm also better positioned to give good advice on studying.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Simply excellent, very engaging. This course had the biggest impact so far on my learning. Barbara is kind of an example to follow, the tips and tricks are easy to apply and powerful. The right amount of theory helps understanding what's going on. Do it - you won't regret it (says an otherwise very, very sceptic learner¡¦)!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I would highly recommend this course for everyone who likes learning new things, but doesn't know how to organize himself and to deal with the procrastination. The course reveals how does our brain works so that we get the most out of studying. For those who is new in MOOCs I would recommend to start with this amazing course!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I found this course well-paced and informative. As a psychotherapist working with adolescents in high school, the course information will help me work with them on procrastination, study habits, test taking, etc.. Professor Oakley was upbeat and inspiring. Well documented strategies and information sources. Well worth the time!!!!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This is the best course that I have completed on coursera. Instructor barbara is full of life and energetic. I am a computer science student and have completed several other courses related to my subject on different platforms (edx,udacity etc) and this is the only non technical course that I have taken and it was worth of it.

review_contents:

The techniques taught in this course are incredibly helpful, most of which I've been able to apply to my current job. I am now confident that I have the tools necessary to pursue any degree/career.

Thank you!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This course really helped me gain confidence in learning and gave me valuable insight. Not only did it show me why my previous ways of learning were ineffective up until now, but it also armed me with some simple and easy techniques that are already paying off. I also really love Barbara's whimsy! Great course!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Very good class and very practical too. I learned many useful ways to improve my memory and learning. title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I think everyone should take this course. The instructors -- especially Barbara Oakley -- was a wonderful (and fun!) instructor. title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I would recommend 'Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects' to others. It has helped to understand my flaws and will help me in future. title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Dr. Oakley is a phenomenally excellent instructor. She even goes the extra mile and provides weekly emails after the course is completed. These emails provide links to do many informative topics from which I am learning so much. I am deeply appreciative of all her hard work.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Excellent course for the largest possible audience. Life-long-learning is a necessity for today's knowledge workers. We all (should) spend a lot of time in our life on learning. title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents:
Very interesting course. I learned a few things I'm hoping to make me a better learner. I plan to go back and read all the optional material and listen to the interviews of the successful people.

I'm going to make my 10th grade son take this course over the summer.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Excellent tool for being smart about how to learn. I gained so many tips from reducing procrastination to sharpening memory to better ways for test taking to value of tests in learning to value of recall to difference between defuse learning and focused learning etc.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: What a great course! The information regarding chunking, and the Pomodora technique along with the breathing technique and of course rewarding yourself all make perfect sense and will help me go far in the lifelong learning I plan to do. Thank you Dr. Oakley, et al!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I audited this course (because I could not afford the certificate) and found it very helpful. I wish I could have had its benefits 60 years ago! At 74, I know I would have retained so much more over my years of learning. My thanks to all involved, especially Barbara.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I loved this course. It is helping me a lot in learning. Though, its easier said than done. It takes lots of hard work and practice to get accustomed with those tactics and maintain efficiency. Its quite hard, but the practices mentioned in course are really helpful.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: The course is really great. It gave me insights about my memory works, about how handle the procrastination and how effectively take the tests. There are a lot of useful topics and tools which I have implemented immediately. Thanks to creators for a big work!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This is a perfect beginner course for anyone interested in improving their learning skills. The materials mentioned in the course are generally known, however the insight of the materials is what made this course such an excellent course. Highly recommended.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents:
Fantastic course, completed in 2 weeks. Really took something away from this and looking forward to using the techniques discussed.

Bought Barbara's accompanying book and it is excellent, delves into this MOOC in a lot more detail, also well worth a look.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I realised that while we sometimes do know what is wrong, like a habit of procrastination, we don't necessarily know how to over-come it. Learning how to learn is a useful and interesting course to take to not only understand, but improve your brain activities.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: The best MOOC I've taken; the learnings are straight-forward and applicable for day-to-day life. Loved the two trainers; Barb's passion and enthusiasm is infectious and Terry's sincerity was clear (and his keenness for everyone to do more exercise!). Thank you

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Most helpfull advice on learning how to learn that will increase your motivation, efficiency and confidence in your knowledge. Presented are easy techniques that you would not think of yourself, but work, and more importantly, the science behind them.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents:
The brevity and clarity of the videos is perfectly judged, the science immediately translatable into practice. Stories, analogies, metaphors and expert interviews make it crystal clear how our brains learn best. This course is outstanding.

Neil Bromiley

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: I audited this course and found it to be very helpful. I wish I had been able to take it 60 years ago! Now 74, I know that I would have been able to retain far, far more had I had these helpful tips. My thanks to all involved, especially Barbara.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: As the title say, they give you powerful mental tools, it just all make sense, i really love this course and i think it should be shown in school and colleges, this will help me for me entire life of learning, gracias Barb, Terry y a todo el equipo! :)

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This is my first MOOC learning experience and it is just amazing. I like Barbara's way of delivering the materials which makes it mostly enjoyable. I look forward to completing my certification and embark on a new learning journey. Bravo!

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: Excellent way to undestand how we learn new things and the techniques that helps us to perform better, understand nad move on in our learning. Easy to understand the course and always interesting supporting material. I trully enjoyed taking it

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: This is a wonderfully well-presented course with useful insights for learners of any field. There are tons of extra resources for those who want to dig deeper, and I love the Friday newsletters that make me feel like part of a community.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: It is an amazing course. This kind of information should actually be taught in high school. I would highly recommend this course, whether you are a fulltime student or just taking one course, no matter the subject you are interested in.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents:
The course is very interesting: well organized, well paced and not stressful at all.

The subject matter is of great importance to anyone, be it young or old.

I highly recommend it. It will improve the life of everyone who takes it.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects
review_contents: A very important course no matter what stage of life you are at. I wish I learnt this during my school days. I really thank the creators of this wonderful video for helping to radically change my whole approach towards learning.

title: Learning How to Learn: Powerful mental tools to help you master tough subjects

review_contents: I liked the instructor a lot. He was very easygoing with no assumptions and delivered a great performance. I loved his humorous approach and he made a difficult topic very easy. Kudos to him and uni of illinois for designing such a great course. Would love to study again with both.

title: Financial Evaluation and Strategy: Investments
review_contents: Great course! The instructor really knows his stuff and covers exactly what I was interested in learning . The material is concise and easy to follow.

title: Cloud Computing Concepts, Part 1
review_contents: Course materials were good and coherent. The programming assignment was not prepared well. After all I find it very informative.

title: High-Impact Business Writing
review_contents: Seems like there was very little effort to create the online course. Certainly, little effort to proofread. Slides are full of errors. Irony.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This course is a very nicely put together. Lots of real world examples of digital marketing. I would also like the team to put together a summary page of the course, as the basics go a long way in this specialization, and ahead.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great overview of how new digitals tool are changing how we need to approach marketing now and in the future. (Not necessarily an introduction to digital marketing)

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: It was really good, it exceeded my expectations. I really enjoyed how the course was structured, as well as the interviews on campus, they were very interesting. The examples from real world companies were accurate. I recommend it!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
I have just completed the course. A great course with exciting insights about cutting-edge technologies and thrilling case-studies.

I have been spending about 6-8 hours to watch videos and working thoroughly on case-studies.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This course was better than I expected! I have truly learned a new set of skills and can't wait to start using them. I highly recommend this course to anyone in any Marketing Position. You will definitively learn!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
I really enjoyed learning this way. Prof Aric is really great and clear. Examples and exercises are interesting, even if on my speciality (the music business) I had to disagree on one point, but I can be wrong!

Thanks

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is the first MOOC I have participated in for credit. I found the information informative and useful. I invested 5-7 hours on each module. I would recommend this course to a colleague.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: An excellent, engaging, varied and interesting course. A great way to update my marketing degree and get some insight into the digital world of marketing and the constantly changing market.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great course that I would recommend to anyone involved in Marketing. I particularly liked the part with peer reviews, where I could learn also from peer's experience from around the world!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Best course if you want to understand digital marketing, I must say it's well structured by prof Aric. He is always active in discussion forum to answer. In a way double thumbs up!!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great great course. Will recommend it to all. Dr. Aric is simply great, in terms of explaining the marketing concepts, and the assignments provided a lot of insights as well.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Interesting mix of perspectives on how marketing has changed by going digital. Surprising to learn about co-creation and 3D printing in a marketing course!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Excellent course content and well presented. The course helps you to know the latest trends in digital marketing. I have learned a lot from this course.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Very good course indeed! Exceeds my expectations. Thank you very much Professor Aric. I got a new perspective from the course.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: It was one of the best learning experience for me, accompanied with application of theoretical concepts in real life case studies.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
Easy to follow

Well estructure and with lost of insights for going deeper if wanted

Thanks so much amazing work I will follow more!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I just finished the course and found it very interesting. This was the first Coursera course I have taken. Thanks Aric.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: It gives the student a whole new view of current scenario on marketing and how the whole concept is changing!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is the first course I'm taking on Coursera. I'd say the course is very good, light (not difficult), informative and very well organized. Content was greatly structured. I've learned new things and had fun with the practical exercises and case discussions. The team was very responsive and did great at handling all the little hick ups that came up along the way. I recommend the course.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Let me explain just how great this course is. I have a bachelor's degree, two graduate degrees including an MBA, multiple certificates, and have attended hundreds of workplace training events. This course has been, without question, the most enjoyable learning experience I have ever had. It isn't that those learning experiences were that bad, it's that this course is truly THAT GOOD.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This was not my first online course but I have no doubt to confirm that was the best. It completely exceeded my expectations and that this is not something that happens very often. What I liked more? The different scenes for the classes, the interviews to other proffesor and, of course, Ari certainly has a talent for making the most interesting classes.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: If I say I got addicted to the course would not be enough. Prof. Aric calm, poised, easy paced voice helped us to understand the concept of 4 Ps as applied to Digital Marketing very well. I highly recommend this course as a basic to understand Digital Marketing and to know that Digital Marketing is not just Digital Promotion but more than that. Best Wishes.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
A needed update in marketing concepts, i recommend for the ones who finish marketing studies years ago and now need a refresh on the changes in each of the P's in a digital era.

The course it's very practical, the assignments are great, always new and relevant topics/cases. Prof. Aric is a great guy, looking forward for others courses with him.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This course was somewhat slow placed for those that are tech/digital savvy or already working in the industry, but for anyone looking to learn more a great starting point. Professor Aric does a great job explaining the concepts and making them as simple as possible. Looking forward to the rest of the courses in the Digital Marketing Certification.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great course! Information provided is concise and to the point, numerous real world examples are used which helps students in understanding the theory. The course leader has very engaging voice (which helps, as I usually find it hard to focus on video lectures) and every phrase carries important information, not a minute wasted. I totally recommend!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is a great foundational course. It not only tells you about the current technologies but also gives insights about how these latest technologies have the potential to disrupt industries. Its assignments are quite engaging and let you experience the current ongoings in the world firsthand. I definitely recommend this course for a good foundation.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Thanks Prof Aric and everyone who helped in formulating this course. Its an awesome course and very well structured. Being from a digital agency background I would certainly refer this course to anyone who wants to learn digital marketing. Hope to keep in touch with prof Aric and everyone who made this a rewarding learning experience.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is a great course because the professor has put TONS of thought and work into it. You will immediately notice that the course is very well organized and flows as it should. There is the right mix of case studies, conceptual information, and actual practice involved. The material is relevant and useful. Absolutely recommended.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is the first time I actually completed a course I started on Coursera (cost was possibly a motivation). The course provided an interesting perspective on disruptions to marketing mix. Material and activities were engaging. Quizzes were a bit simple. Peers reviews were fine but there was little constructive feedback.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: The course was very informative.It actually helped me a lot in understanding the digital marketing and the concepts of the same.also the lectures and assignments were a great fun ! Extremely happy ..Thanks to coursera for bringing this opportunity to me ...looking forward to even more such specialisations. ..

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I really enjoyed the coursera course on digital marketing. The coursera introduces one to the digital trends on marketing 4Ps. The depth of coverage and the idea to introduce people to wide array of things happening in marketing is welcome. This course is very good and would recommend all to take the course

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great course covering some of the important aspects of digital marketing as well as giving enough room for the new and emerging technologies that is changing the way brands and marketers work. The professor has a very easy style and brings in experts from various fields as part of discussions. Good intro class.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
Lovely class, both fun and helpful. Very innovative way of teaching from the teacher and his collaborators, with lots of interviews and readings and case studies.

Its useful for both professionals in the field or for regular customers to understand more about this digital world we live in.

Andrei

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I have an MBA from the late 90's, so this was a great refresher course that walks through the 4 P's and provides updates on how they have changed given the rise of digital tools. It was not overly rigorous, but did require ~4 weeks of engagement with others via assignments. I recommend this course!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: No better way to learn about Digital Marketing than in a digital class. Learning a lot about how the digital world is shaping the way in which Marketers must think in order to capitalize this ever growing and changing market. A great combination of video lectures and real life case studies.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Interesting courses and if you have an interest in the marketing, especially in the digital world, it's certainly a courses to follow. Interesting exercises, well done videos and a teacher with whom you can talk and believe me it's not always the case, I recommend it without hesitation.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: The course really gives you innovative and practical insights on how digital tools are reshaping the way of doing businesses and marketing online; allowing you to prepare yourself as a marketer and as a customer on the ongoing shift of power, within the marketplace, from firms to customers.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
Great organized coursework with an inviting stream of lectures.

Letting people from all over the world share their view points, grade and review projects, makes a huge difference and takes learning to a whole new level. Thumbs up to the team and especially Prof. Aric.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I really enjoyed the course. It was a great introduction to the concept of digital marketing. I particularly liked the chunking of the course information. It was structured in a way that allowed me to work on it before I left for work in the morning. Well done!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Thanks Professor. The course was really interesting for me. I learned new concepts and topics very actualized. The cases and the interviews really enriched the concepts and the tendences. Congratulations! really is the best way to learn and be actualized.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I really enjoyed this course that talks about the 4-P concept applied to the new digital tools available. Besides, Aric Rindfleisch is an interesting and knowledgable teacher. The case study and the exercice are fun and diversified. I highly recommand this course.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Best course I've done on coursera by far! It is very interesting, self paced, and the videos include interesting cases. It is very centered on new technologies and introduces lots of new concepts. The instructor is very good and I really enjoyed the videos.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: The best decision I made this year was to enroll for this course. The course content is useful, updated and the lectures videos are full of real examples. Plus, the professor has a lot of experience, and the suggestions of readings are really great.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Excellent overview of digital marketing concepts--the exercises are easy and practical. The only way to make it better would be to apply the skills in some sort of final project for the course (there is one for the entire learning series/certificate).

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
I would recommend this course. The material is very well presented. The case studies and exercises are well designed.... and some great learning happens!

Above all, it is very enjoyable.... so go ahead and have some fun while learning :)

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
I love this course, and i promise you that you will love it. You will learn about new digital marketing concept that will stimulates your creativity, and of course it will change the way you think.

Thank you Prof. Aric Rindfleisch

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great course, interesting cases and exercises. Learn a lot about digital marketing, how the world its changing. How firms and consumers are nowadays changing the perspective of the traditional marketing through digitalizing.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is great course which I highly recommend. Well-crafted and designed. The material is fresh and engaging! I enjoyed the fact that the teacher exposes the student to different ideas and current trends in the present.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I have just started on this course and feel it is a relevant topic for anybody interested in marketing in today's world as everything around us gets digitized. Will add more on the course as I progress in it. Thanks!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: It is very well organized with interesting practical tasks in order to better understand and remember the cases discussed during the lessons. I'll continue with the next course of the Digital Marketing specialization.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
superb course, very up to date and inspiring...it is also academically very well founded.

The Red Laser app that had to be used for the last excercises wasn't supported anymore...so try to adress this issue

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great course. Digital marketing was new to me and with a combination of Prof Aric Rindfleisch's informative videos, which included real-life examples, and readings, I really learned a lot.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Interesting and very informative. The practical assignments were appropriate and helped to reinforce the course content. I feel more confident and equipped to use digital platforms

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Excellent course! The new concepts of digital marketing which appear in this course are up to date. The teacher, the lessons and the exercises keep you interested in this area.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Awesome course, mind bending and eye opening! I learned so much about the shift to a world more and more digital. A world that brings challenges and lots of opportunities. Go get it!

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: fantastic course! Great view on marketing and how it can be used in the digital world. I recommend it, prof. Aric was a great teacher and highly implicated with the course.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: This is an excellent course for marketing professionals who want to upgrade their skills and be current and relevant. I highly recommend this course. Thank you! Karen

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: A great program! This course is a complete actualization about how marketing is changing with the progress of digital tools and social media. Absolutely recommended.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
Exceded my expectations.

It was very enlightening.

I get bored very easily when taking these courses on coursera but this one wasn't the case. Very enganging.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: I am glad i came across this course its really an eye opener for me and the exercises they help a lot to get hands on experience. Plus the Lecturer is a great guy.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents:
This is a great course to get a bird's view of Marketing and in particular digital marketing.

It will be a good course for beginners and experts alike.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Great course from University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign as usual. Lot of stuff to learn especially for people coming from non-marketing background.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Entertaining and very complete course on digital marketing. I liked the hands-on exercises, which were very detailed and fun. Loved it.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: Excellent - great intro and some good insights into what is happening in the digital space. I look forward to the follow up series.

title: Marketing in a Digital World
review_contents: The entire course was very well put together - from intros to case studies down to the assignments. Prof. Aric Rindfleisch was great!

title: Code Yourself! An Introduction to Programming

title: Code Yourself! An Introduction to Programming

review_contents: This course was a disaster for me - attempting to download the Roby software resulted in changed software from the lecture which I simply couldn't get to work as each command tried according to the lecture resulted in a different result due no doubt to the software being updated - a dreadful mess but like they say 'ya pays peanuts, ya gets monkeys' bye Coursera

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: This is not a $79 course and is a waste of money. Coursera needs to review the courses before stamping a price on it. You would think universities would know how to teach without simply reading from slides. This course needs an overhaul with a real programmer teaching the course. The teaching style needs to be updated also.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: Good course. The instructions for submitting the assignments need to be reviewed, it took excess to submit each assignment. Additionally consider using a standard development environment like https://c9.io or using EC2 the way the start-up engineering class does https://class.coursera.org/startup-001; it seems this would remove some of the questions from the discussion boards.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: The course is finished with interest , but I think it is not necessary to give in the first part of the course introduction to Rails, and pay more attention to Ruby and TDD. A second part of the course I think that it is necessary to increase for one week and to transfer part of the introduction to Rails there.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents:
swoosh ... ruby ... slurp ... heroku .... swoosh/slurp .... controller .... slurp ... slurp ....

add this to horrible TA's ... you have the description of this course ...

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: The course should be more hands-on from the lecturer's end. There is no point for a lecturer to read from his power-point to adult and the core practical is ignored. It was not helpful to me, I dropped and bought a book and did it on my own along with Youtube videos.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: The course could be more divided. Since it focus one week in ruby and one week in rails its very demanding in terms of classes and assignments. Maybe if the course had more weeks (around 6?) it could be more divided and treat more specific each topic.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: The course material was great. The exercises ensured that I am able to implement what I learnt. Finally learning Ruby on Rails doesn't hurt.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: This course was a as real as you may need I consider you can go into more basic details of how the Ruby on Rails Framework worworks for a beginner.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: The lectures are well structured and clear. Being not a complete beginner in Rails, I learned a lot while following along with all the assignments. However, their descriptions could be a little bit more detailed - sometimes I found myself lost. In such cases course's community is of a great help.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents:
Course moves too fast. The course is not designed to give you an intuitive understanding of Ruby and/or Ruby on Rails. I have up after the end of Week 2 when I realized I did not truly understand the majority of it.

There is no live coding either. Live coding is essential for web tutorials.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents:
I missed the last assignment partly due to lack of time, also that it suddenly jumped into Rails without much preparation - that was a shame.

I regret that there were no PDFs for this course, as I didn't have time to watch the videos.

There really should be a rethink of the last assignment.

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: the quality of the contents are awesome compared to another learning platforms, and the way of the homeworks are made (using rspec) to test the code that you build is great and seems like the real world

title: Ruby on Rails: An Introduction
review_contents: It's a very good effort but I think there is more content that should be cover about controllers and views. Also, showing ho to code a real app in some short videos would be ideal.

review_contents: Great course to learn simple gui programming. It is a beginner's Python course. I wasn't a beginner in Python, but I had no gui experience. Course was a lot of fun. Lectures were interesting and well done. Course material was released on time, every week. Coding interface (CodeSkulptor) was very good, and allowed for a lot of flexibility. Certainly one of the best courses I have taken so far.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Wonderful class with instructive and helpful teachers, covers a lot of material on basic programming leading up to more complex game building. Whether you are mildly interested in programming, have no experience, or just want some enhancement on your previous knowledge, this is a great course for you. It was a lot of fun taking this class, and I recommend it to aspiring programmers of all ages!

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Good experience! I really enjoyed the part I. I loved the mini-projects. Classes were easy to follow and you can feel quite "dangerous" after a few weeks from a beginner. However Part II is too tough, they don't really explain everything properly, many leaks of information and you need to struggle with every single line of the code to reach the mini-project at the end of each week. That's a pity!

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: I had so much fun completing this course. The instructors have a relaxed, enjoyable style. Their passion and humour come through in every lecture. They're worked hard to make this course work. It's not for the faint-hearted. Many fall by the wayside but if you stick to it and work your way logically through the examples, exercises, quizzes and mini-projects, I'm sure you'll have heaps of fun too.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Great class! It willl probably be too easy if you've done some programming before, but even so if you are not familiar with event-driven programming it's a really nice introduction. The videos, exercises and templates and forums give you everything you need to get the projects done. Also the codeskulptor tool is a really awesome tool that makes it easy to get started and get working right away.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: It has been very helpful for me to take this class. Although mainly focused on building games there's a bunch of python programming tips that will definitely be useful for other applications. I have to admit that could not complete all the assignments in time, but got so hooked to this class that finished them pass the deadline. Thanks to the instructors, Rice and Coursera for the initiative.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This is a spectacular introductory course to the world of programming and Python. Joe and Scott are marvelous lecturers, finding a wonderful medium between making the course material simple and easy to learn and giving a thorough understanding of the material. They also inject their class with fun and laughs -- definitely a welcome treat. Beyond recommended for those interested in programming.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This class was fantastic! The lectures, quizzes, and mini-projects were all extremely well devised to add knowledge and programming techniques at a reasonable pace. It was a lot of work, but well worth the effort. The professors were clear as well as entertaining, and very available on the discussion forums to help get past any difficulties in understanding. All in all it was a great experience.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Excellent course that goes through the material at a good pace for beginners or those who may have a little experience in other languages. The projects were fun and you felt like you really were accomplishing things. Those with more experience/knowledge can extend the basic project to incorporate additional functions. Really great teachers who explained concepts well and made things interesting.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: A good class to learn the basics of Python. Implemented using their online "development environment", which is good because students don't have to struggle through installations on their own machine, but does leave a bit to be desired in python skills applicable outside of the class. Professors kept the lectures and projects fun and engaging, and the class had an active forum community.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This is the first online class I've taken, and the only negative thing I have to say about it is that I have a feeling any others I take in the future will be some degree of disappointing in comparison. I thought the instructors did a fantastic job and I would take any class they offered (probably even one in something I was already familiar with) just for the enjoyment of participating in it.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: I learned a lot about the Python programming language in this class. In fact, I started using what I know and teaching my 11 year old daughter about computer programming with Python. She started reading this book called Hello World! from Manning Publications that teaches kids about creating games in Python. Also, I may have he take this class depending on how well she does learning from the book.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Not to downplay any of the instructional videos and other materials (all great!), but I think CodeSkulptor really makes this class outstanding. CodeSkulptor is a programming environment that the instructors developed to make testing Python code easy and (nigh) platform independent - even better, it allows easy storage and submission of students' programs, *and* makes peer evaluation much simpler.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Excellent balance between video lecture, short quizzes, and weekly projects to keep you motivated and learning step by step throughout the course. The projects involve making games, so they are fun to share with family and friends, Although people with no programming experience can learn from this course, people with some experience will have an easier time. I spent ~10 hours/ week on this course.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Highly recommended. Great Lectures. Well prepared. Great projects. Great people in the Forum. Codeskulptor is simple, yet effective. I built an Asteroids program, and I can tweak any aspect of it. I'm an engineer, 57, and this was a great way to keep my ancient programming skills intact. I will take any class offered by these professors. This is the best of my three Coursera classes.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: It was a wonderful learning experience with Dr. Joe Warren and Dr. Scott Rixner. The video lectures, quizzes and mini-projects were very relevant to the course and provided an excellent learning opportunity. The discussion forums were also very helpful in interacting with the instructors and fellow students. I would recommend this course to anyone who is enthusiastic about learning Python!

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: I think this class is very good for beginners who want a fun and compelling introduction to programming. By teaching programming through making games, you get gratification by seeing your work up and running as something tangibly interesting and fun. The professors do a good job of explaining the material and making lectures interesting, and the exercises build well upon previous material.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: I've taken several free online classes, many related to programming. This was the best class I've ever taken. Joe, Scott, and John are three great personalities and educators. Each emphasized a specific area of expertise and played off of each other extremely well. It's great to to truly enjoy the educational experience. When I completed one week, I could wait for the next week to begin.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This class is great for both experienced programmers and beginners. No prior experience with Python is required to take this course and be able to complete it. Of course, having prior programming experience and/or experience with Python will enable you to complete the quizzes and class projects in a shorter time than otherwise, and probably to be able to take out even more from this class.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Introduction to interactive programming is an excellent way to learn how to programm. It teaches Python - a nice and clean programming language. Throughout the course you are building games, from easy ones in the beginning to the more complex and exciting in the end. Teachers of this course did their best to put together a solid and fundamental course, so it's definitely worth taking.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Very fun and enjoyable class. I did have previous programming experience so the class was a bit easier for me. One of the things I liked best about this course is that the assignments were fun programs/games that I enjoyed trying to build when I was first learning to program. The kind of programs I don't get to write at my current job. It brought that element of fun back to my programming.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: A very good course to be honest . Yeah , and the worklload isn't that much . You can get almost instant help in the forums . One question I asked was replied minutes later. Also , the videos are very well organized and NOT 'boring' , as they contain funny content as well. A good course and encourage you to take it , I took it with no prior programming experience and got alot after its end.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Really reset my expectations for online courses and taking them seriously. My mood eventually went from "Ugh . . . . . I HAVE to do my project...ugh."" to "I GET to do my project, and I just thought of a new way to really spice it up!". From nearly missing deadlines, to nearly missing deadlines because I couldn't stop upgrading my code. Check it out, I'm glad I did.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Excellent course with top-class instructors. I joined this course after seeing their demo class. I haven't seen anything like this before. As for me,I know programming but average at coding. I could manage myself do the first three projects and am proud of it. Later on the projects became a little tougher and challenging for me, but still I tried doing it. Thoroughly enjoyed this course.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Excellent class if you want to learn Python. Though this class uses a refined version of Python with custom modules that are probably not available in standard Python versions. its educative to the purposes of knowing Python and its capabilities. The instructors are highly lucid in their presentations are there are a lot of online tools (forums, etc...) to help you through the class.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents:
In this course you will learn python while enjoying making your own games, and teachers are funny. I really recommend it.

Aprenderas python de forma divertida programando tus propios juegos, y te los pasaras bien con lo profesores en sus videos a la par que practicas ingles (el audio, ya que los subtitulos los puedes poner en castellano muchas veces). Curso totalmente recomendado.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Course content is perfect organized in a increasingly difficulty level. Instructors are really funny and very resourceful which makes this class very interesting. We also get to make very interesting games in such a short amount of time which is really a confidence booster. I simply loved this course and definitely recommend this course for beginners as well as intermediate developers.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This class is awesome. The discussion forums are a tremendous resource when you are struggling with questions on quizzes and mini-projects. I definitely enjoyed the instructors and their efforts to make the class fun and interesting. I feel more confident with my skills and am grateful for the ability to have taken this course online from anywhere I could get an internet connection.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: Class was well taught, engaging, and did a great job teaching a real and useful programming language. Be forewarned that the suggested time required is spot on - you WILL need 7-10 hours a week for this course! There are two quizzes and a coding project every week. That said - it is worth it. I learned a lot and am looking forward to the next offering from Joe, Scott, John, and Stephen!

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: I really liked the way the topics were introduced in a logical manner and the quizzes and practice exercises. I ensured to do the quizzes and the practice exercises before attempting the mini-projects. This made it easier for me to understand the concepts. I also found the step-by-step instructions very useful.They were clear and unambiguous. Finally, it was good fun and highly satisfying.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This was a very fun way to learn how to program simple games in Python and was also a great introduction to object oriented programming. The professors did a great job keeping the videos to point while staying entertaining and engaging. I would recommend this to anyone interested in learning a computer language for the first time or someone who has programmed before, but new to Python.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: It was interesting and challenging. We built awesome games, nailed it with Asteroids in the last week of the course. The assignments were rather difficult but you could ask for help in the discussion forums or even send your code to Code Clinic when you were stuck at some point of programming the assignments. There is nothing to be criticized about the class. It was awesome.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: The content of the class is excellent. I was a novice in Python but now I can say with confidence that I have learnt Python programming to a good extent and can further built on from here on the platform provided by this class. The instructors are excellent and they have explained to concepts very nicely and intuitively. I strongly recommend this class for Python beginners.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: This class was both a great learning experience as well as a load of fun! It struck an excellent balance between being challenging enough to keep you going but not too challenging lest it be discouraging through excessive difficulty. I now feel very confident in my ability to code in Python and to continue to learn, and I have a great portfolio to share and continue building upon!

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents:
The class was delivered in a challenging way with an interesting proportion of teaching, "hands on" and FUN. The teachers were really good, and you could see and feel the experience in the class delivery. The mini projects structure was well organized, including steps and clear explanations of the requirements.

Love the class and would recommend to anyone else.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: As an experienced programmer that wanted to learn Python, I was not sure what to expected from the course, but found that it was an excellent learning opportunity. The course was well organized, the lectures were excellent, and the activities provided a challenging environment to learn. I would highly recommend this course to anyone interested in getting started with Python!

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
review_contents: A very well-presented course providing an introduction to programming, using Python as the language. They have created a fantastic online interactive Python programming environment which provides a basic GUI library to get a beginner involved with fun projects with visible results. For experienced programmers, this is a good, but simple, introduction to the Python language.

title: An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python (Part 1)
