review_contents: This is an excellent course with transformational power. Business schools typically teach us how to manage almost every resource (money, property, competitors, customers, employees, etc) but little attention is paid to the management of our most valuable asset - ourselves. I am most grateful to Raj for providing such a clear roadmap to happiness.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Pretty amazing that a course like this exists! The course material is something we could all be more mindful of, and although an ongoing path, this course teaches us many tools and habits to develop and nourish the happiness within us. Definitely feeling more enlightened and full of spirit thanks to Professor Raj and the many brilliant minds his course has exposed us to!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: A very common sense approach to Happiness. I had a great time doing this course and am glad I signed up for so much fun. It would be too dramatic to say "this course will change your life" but yes, you learn a lot about yourself and at the end of the course, you definitely learn what you can do to stay happy/pursue happiness.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Without doubt, this is the most refreshing course during the otherwise 'hectic' one year MBA Programme at ISB. From the course content and exercises/assignments, to the brilliantly engrossing classroom sessions - every memory and learning from this course leaves a permanent imprint in one's mind. This is one subject that can blatantly claim to be a learning for life!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: This is the best course I ever took! It is all based in scientific research, very well organized, fun, easy to follow and effective - my happiness levels increased during the course. Excellent! I recommend to everybody. I thank the entire team involved =)

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: The aspects of happiness taught in this course are based on research and not on religion, esoterism, mysticism (...). The videos are well made and the course's head, Prof. Raj, not only seems to be a happy person himself, he excels in his role and provides a superb learning experience. This course is exceeding all my expectations.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Such a great class for everyone to take! Whether you feel as though you're happy and very in touch with yourself and what makes you happy, or you really haven't thought about it - this course is an excellent way to learn how to improve your life!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: If you've taken a social psychology course, you know most of this already and won't find this course that useful. It takes a fair amount of effort since all points are belaboured. Cultural and individual differences barely acknowledged. A highly enthusiastic and articulate instructor is the course's major asset.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: It appears to be a fun personal development course with good use of sound cues, music, instructional video presentation. It is easy to follow. I did not find it challenging or rigorous, so a certificate would not mean anything, since the end goal is your own personal development, not a certificate. I am happy to drop it.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: A very good course. My only suggestion would be to extend it for another week or two. The amount of work and time required for the last week didn't allow me to work to the best of my abilities. I should have gone back to review much of the earlier sessions before beginning on the final quiz and the final question set.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: If you are considering taking this course please go ahead and do it. A good investment of your time. Engaging and enjoyable with very simple tasks that are actually very helpful. Huge thanks to the instructors for putting this together. Long may you all be happy :)

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: The course content is very helpfull , easy to follow and practice. Videos are easy to follow, short, and atractive. It is a habbit changing course if you really practice the exercises. The final exam is like a summary to all course, by doing the exam you will check your self if you learn all content.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: I started it because I was depressed, but it was so much more than just a way to fight depression. Useful practices, easy-to-do exercises, a lot of analysis of most prominent studies in the field alongside a lot of other opportunities to dig deeper and do further research on the topic. Bravo!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Such a beautiful course that is much needed at this time. It is amazing to see the enormous effort and research that has gone into the making of this truly dynamic learning experience. I feel blessed to have stumbled upon this course and have learned so much. Prof Raj and team, you are all amazing!!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: A must for everyone who is smart enough to understand that happiness is as scientific a course as any other. Prof. Raj has done a great job of assimilating vast information and research into an easy step by step process for a peaceful and content life alongside successful careers.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: The best course on happiness, personnel development and understanding the meaning of life !! Wonderful Professor Raj and wonderful experiment, statistic and guest interview. Life changing course with happiness measurement and understanding the real meaning of life and happiness !!

many interesting reaserches and studies.

Lessons are built smartely.

Definetely improves happiness levels if you take it seriously and do homework.

A course to go back to from time to time.

review_contents: A great course, with great involvement from the teacher and assistants. The video lectures are very well structured and clear. The happiness exercises were very well created and easy to follow. The quizzes and final exam were of medium difficulty so that anyone can pass this course. This was one of the best course on Coursera. Thank you Prof Raj, Thank you ISB and Thank you Coursera.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: This course came at a time in my life when I was ready to accept it and I loved it. I loved how Professor Raj turned what is usually considered a subjective topic into a scientific study. He even incorporated spirituality. All of the sources he quoted were well spoken and very knowledgeable in their fields. All of it made sense. I enjoyed every minute of this course!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Prof Raj - i don't really know what to say. His course of Creativity and Leadership at ISB was the highlight of my year. What i love about his style of teaching is that it was preachy and respected our imperfections and most importantly involve a ton of introspection which was just the doze i needed. More power to you Prof. Looking forward to attending these lectures.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: This course is simply amazing! Thank you prof. Raj, it was a pleasure to fallow your course. Everything was good explained with the simple words and easy to understand. U gave us the good base and now it is up to us to start changing our bad habits and be more mindful and happy. "Be the change you want to see in the world". Looking forward to reading your book!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents:
Away from the clutter of money optimization courses of MBA, this course offered a completely new perspective of looking forward in life through a logical window towards a happy life.

The arguments presented , the interactive videos and Dr Raj's style of teaching makes this course a must for me. Looking forward for his book on this this research.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: This is a great course which has been well researched and highlights many experts from various universities who definitely help to enrich the course contents. Prof Raj delivered the course using language which is easy to understand. Many thanks to Prof Raj and Coursera for making the course available. I will definitely recommend this course.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: A fascinating journey came to an end. The course was an eye opener - as it cleared many misconceptions regarding HAPPINESS. The activities & exercises were very interesting. Above all it was Prof. Raj who made the big impact with his energetic and humorous delivery. Recommend taking this course for understanding all about being Happy.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Prof. Raj has great positive energy which he shows during each video and has done a prodigious amount of research which he includes throughout the course. You learn something new each week and have the ability to practice it. An extremely well thought out course extremely well delivered. I was sad when it ended.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: It was a wonderful experience to have learned around this course. All the syllabus, the videos, the exercises done were absolutely amazing and inspired me to continue by applying those to my own life. Professor Raj: Thank you so much for putting it together and inspire us to learn in a relax and enjoyable way.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: By far the best course I have taken. Prof. Raj's delivery of the material is not only lighthearted, entertaining and easy to follow, but also incredibly insightful and captivating. I would gladly, and indeed most likely, take this course all over again, and will definitely recommend it to absolutely everyone.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Great class! I learned so much about happiness that I can apply to my day-to-day life. I've been carrying around my notes with me as reminders and will likely continue to do so. I highly recommend this course for anyone who wants to think more positively and is willing to actively make changes in their life.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: Ideal course for understanding the basic principles of happiness and what separates us from it. The exercises are ingenious and fulfilling, and come with the best of intentions. I recommend this course for anyone interested in questioning happiness and learn more about what we already know: that we are happy.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: I liked the course very much. Dr. Raj is very good explaining the concepts. The course is composed of a very wide and interesting themes and it is not all theorical , but includes many exercises to experience the main aspects discussed. It requires between three to four hours per week. I highly recommend it!!

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: The course was very helpful in giving me practical understanding of happiness and steps to take to become happy. I appreciated all of the scientific documentation and research that we learned about. I highly recommend this course to others. In fact, I keep talking about it to nearly everyone I meet.

title: A Life of Happiness and Fulfillment
review_contents: This is one of the best courses I have ever attended ! Pro. Raj is a rockstar, full of energy. His commitment is infectious. It has made a huge difference to my happiness levels and enabled me to instill great happiness habits. I would whole heartedly recommend this outstanding course to one and all :)

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents:
A solid course from a great instructor. Unlike some of the other courses in the Genomic Data Science Specialization, which have been shallow or poorly taught, this course is challenging (but not undoable) and the lectures are very well organized.

The course is short, so you should not expect to get a full introduction to the field. But for its length, the course delivers a lot.

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents: Good course for all levels. Not much previous experience needed and a good learning curve. Recommended for people of all backgrounds who want to learn how sequencing works.

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents: This was a very nice course. The instructor explained things really well and the problem sets were fun, interesting, challenging enough to be motivating but doable. I had taken the San Diego bioinformatics courses, and this course helped me solidify some of the material that flew by in that other course. Highly recommended!

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents: This course was organized excellently. For a course with a duration of just 4 weeks it covers an amazing amount of required DNA sequencing background material and algorithms. Lectures were great and practicals were amazing since they covered coding of algorithms. Course offers plenty of scope for future learning.

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents: I found the lectures and the assignments to be very helpful and interesting. The course also provided an excuse to learn some of the Python programming language, which I encounter from time to time in my current career.

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents:
Great course.

Thanks to wonderful instructors:

Ben Langmead, PhD and Jacob Pritt.

Highly recommended to all interested in algorithms design in general, applied computer science and modern bioinformatics.

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents: This was the high point of an otherwise dreadful specialization. It was well-taught. And both the exercises & tutorial format were well-suited to the course.

title: Algorithms for DNA Sequencing
review_contents: As any course in both "specializations" from Johns Hopkins, this is a just a random collection of things with no structure. Don't waste your time, you will not learn much.

review_contents: Challenging and rewarding introductory CS course. Downloading the Python interpreter is practically mandatory. My only complaint is that when they show the code he's working on in the videos, it is too small and fuzzy to read.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: In summer last year, I took this course as my first course to learn CS and I was satisfied with the quality and rigor of this course. I learned many CS concepts and did practice with tons of programming exercises. The professor's high quality lectures and active discussion forum were really helpful. I think the high quality of edX platform itself also contributed to my success in this course.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: This course is hard like other MIT courses. Be prepared to work a lot to perform well. A good news that it's not that hard like previous course in functional programming. The second part is about scientific applications of python that is not very common for such courses but natural for MIT. Personally I was highly interested in Monte-Carlo simulations.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: Very useful course, with plenty of practice exercises. Covers programming methods beyond just the python language. A very good introduction, that goes fairly deep into the concepts. I hesitated rating it intermediate, rather than beginner, for this reason: it's a more demanding course than that proposed by University of Michigan (Dr Chuck), for instance.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: Excellent class. It is a very serious introduction to programming, beyond the usual college introductory level. It discusses some data structures and a good number of algorithms. Its programming assignments are challenging. The presentations are exemplary in their precision and rigor. There is not one minute wasted during the lectures.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: I don't consider this an introduction to Python. They expect you to solve some of the problems without giving you the information in the lectures.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: Video and audio quality (thus far) is a little poor by 2015 standards but the course content is deep, engaging and applicable. Both easy and challenging problems are interspersed at just the right intervals to keep you attentive and learning.

title: 6.00.1x: Introduction to Computer Science and Programming Using Python
review_contents: This is an excellent introduction into Computer Science using Python. The instructor is very clear in his explanations and the assignments are challenging, while also good learning experiences. This is a top level MOOC - excellent.

review_contents: I really enjoyed this MOOC. The coursework, while a little demanding at the start, is well-structured and well- paced. It is hard for network beginners. Almost impossible for someone without networking background at all.

But if you know some networking and basic Python, this might be an interesting course for you.

title: Software Defined Networking
review_contents: It was good. but I expected little more information about the northbound and southbound.

title: Metaliteracy: Empowering Yourself in a Connected World
Metaliteracy: Empowering Yourself in a Connected World
Bitcoin and Cryptocurrency Technologies
review_contents:
Excellent course.

Cleanly separates the different pieces that go into making bitcoin, and explains each of them simply and clearly. Covers not only bitcoin and cryptocurrencies, but also the wider implications and applications of the blockchain to non-currency applications.

Highly recommended for anyone interested in bitcoin or the blockchain.

title: Bitcoin and Cryptocurrency Technologies
review_contents:
Very interesting course explaining cryptocurrencies in different aspects. Highly recommended to anyone interested in bitcoins, cryptocurrencies or just normal currencies as well.

As mentioned in other comments, please, note you will not have any types of homework and will not get any statement of accomplishment.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: This course is an algorithms class intended to be the 2nd course taken by CS students at Princeton. From what I could tell the course was pretty true to the actual Princeton class, and the automated grader was great. This algorithms class was well designed and I¡¯ll probably take the follow-up class.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: Great course. Lectures are very well done, best I have seen so far. Programming assignments were also quite good even though they are in Java, which I didn't know at the start of the course. Problem sets were good, but some work could be improve the interface. Everything was on time.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: This is probably one of the best class I took in Algorithm. Yes, the assignments are challenging but you learn quite a bit by just doing so. Furthermore, I found the lectures well done. I find the instructor quite interesting and am motivated to do the next course given by this instructor.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: I found this course quite challenging, but learned a lot. Discussion forums were very helpful, much higher standard than other courses I have taken. I enjoyed the lectures. Looking forward to part II. Lack of Java knowledge does make the course very difficult.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: I read some books and do some classes about algorithms,but I think this class is best way to learn algorithms.Prof Sedgewick explain algorithms and data structures very good.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: I had some programming experience - mostly in Python - when started this course and it was very useful, interesting and inspiring. Prof. Sedgewick is a very good teacher.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: Difficult class, not for beginners. PowerPoint presentation slides are boring. It seems Professor Sedgewick has taught this class so many times that he've got tired of it.

title: Algorithms, Part I
review_contents: Coursework was challenging, but uninteresting. Instructor wasn't entirely engaging and lecture videos just consisted of a reading of the PowerPoint slides.

title: Organizational Analysis (Self-Paced)
review_contents: It was my first MOOC, but I thought it was worth my time. The professor really had put alot of effort into the preparation of this course and I liked his style of teaching.

title: Organizational Analysis (Self-Paced)
review_contents: Engaging, information was clearly delivered and well presented. this course has given me an appetite for more. I highly recommend this one...many thanks.

title: Organizational Analysis (Self-Paced)
review_contents: This course, though full of useful information is very disorganized in comparison to other Coursera experiences.

title: Malicious Software and its Underground Economy: Two Sides to Every Story
review_contents: It's the great course. It let me know more about how the malicious code attack and work and how we identify or response to that code. This course is suitable for the student who has a knowledge about programming, software engineering or information security a little bit.

An Introduction to Consumer Neuroscience & Neuromarketing
review_contents: A very interesting topic. Course was very interesting overall however some lectures were general opinion interviews with experts in the field. Good insight in to a field with huge potential.

title: An Introduction to Consumer Neuroscience & Neuromarketing
review_contents: Currently this course seems to be more of a marketing campaign for neuromarketing tools rather than a scientific discussion of the topic.

title: An Introduction to Consumer Neuroscience & Neuromarketing
review_contents:
Quite interesting course.

However the materials should be better strucutred - interviews should be classified as additional material and not class lectures.

title: An Introduction to Consumer Neuroscience & Neuromarketing
AE1110x: Introduction to Aeronautical Engineering
review_contents:
It worth the efforts, they made the course very entertaining, it is well explained, the use of the virtual blackboard was a big plus, great teachers and staff, so is the community.

I never felt lazy to do the homeworks which are not that easy. They are hard enough so you can check that you really understood the lessons but not that hard.

title: AE1110x: Introduction to Aeronautical Engineering
review_contents:
Very interesting, well explained, not so easy but not impossible. Nice teachers and good community, if you really like aeronautics and have no or basic knowledge I recommend you to take this course.

It took me about 90 hours to complete it.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This is a great course for anyone wishing to learn python programming. The instructors Jen and Paul do a fantastic job of walking you through the fundamentals of Python programming. This course gives you a good foundation to build on for moving into other programming courses. A great course which I highly recommend for anyone who wishes to learn programming in general and Python in particular.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This was a really good introduction to python and programming. I took this course and An Introduction to Interactive Programming in Python at the same time. This class started a little ahead of the other class and really helped me to grasp the concepts in the other class quickly. I recommend both these classes to anyone interested in programming.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Excellent basic programing class in Python language. The professors are presenting the topics in a very simple manner so that I who never had programmng experience previously could easily learn Python. Mind you, if you are a newbie, it will need more than 8 hours per week, but it is worth it if you are interested in Python. Thanks Jen and Paul.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This was a great class! As many have said, the pace was set for beginners, but the assignments were still interesting and provided some challenge to a student with a little programming experience. I appreciated the fact that this course offered a certificate. I am definitely looking forward to "Crafting Quality Code!"

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents:
If you decide to take this class, don't go to the forum.

Every time you will say something in contrast to the majority of the people there, they will start insulting and deriding you, and never replied to your requests.

The TAs, far from helping, are just encouraging this behaviour, and joining the snarky comments.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents:
Fantastic intro to Python programming. Course material well presented. The pace of the course is perfect for beginners, and lays a firm foundation for future advancement.

Video Lectures, written notes, peer discussion forum, regular assessment exercises and assignments.

Highly recommended.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: An excellent course. Very much appreciated the simple to install tools (IDLE). It's more a beginners course, but as a professional programmer it served as an easy way to get up to speed on Python. Looking forward to the future course on "Crafting Quaity Code" !

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Took this simultaneously (sort of) with the Interactive Python class (Coursera - Rice University). Both classes were great. This class truly started at the beginning, and the instructors were wonderful. I WILL take the followup course they are offering next year.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: I've started several MOOCs. Finished only this one and awaiting eagerly the follow-up. The professors know precisely what they are doing - both in the field of CS-teaching and in the field of conducting a MOOC. LTP1 is an exemplary course in every respect!

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This is a truly excellent introduction to programming in Python, particularly for anyone that has little or no programming experience. I recommend this course to anyone beginning programming, and the follow up course "Crafting Quality Code".

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This class is an excellent way to learn how to program, both teachers were really good at explaining topics. And I totally recommend this course to the kind of person who doesn't knowe anything at all about computers as well as beginners in the field.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This is a great class on introduction to programming with Python. Great pace, great contents, great instructors! You really learn to program plus you get a certificate. All of these somehow make you feel like the effort you put in really pays off.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Terrific introduction to programming. Don't be fooled by the short lectures, in which every sentence is packed with information you can't afford to miss. If you've never programmed before, and want to be challenged some, this is for you.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This is a fantastic class. The professors are very good at explaining how things work. It builds the foundation of python programming. I thoroughly enjoyed the classes. Thank you professors for your hard work and providing the free class.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Very good class. A great first step to learning how to program. Instructors were very clear in presenting concepts and ideas. Lectures were well reinforced with quizzes, assignments an in-video questions with immediate feedback.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Great class for those who want to learn the basics of python. Well explained videos and it's filled with examples and homework which teach you a lot. This is great for beginners and those who just want to go back to basics.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This class was a really great introduction to programming in python. The professors were fantastic and they both did a really good job explaining the material very clearly. I recommend this class very highly.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: The course is an excellent choice for beginners. The teachers were great. I really appreciated Visualizer. It did help me a lot in understanding how the program works step by step. It's a great tool for beginners.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: If you have never done Python programming or programming at all, this is a great introductory course. Even if you have done some basic programming you may still pick up a few tips. Well worth the time.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This is a great class for anyone who wants to learn programming. Jen and Paul are great instructors, they explain things in a way that everyone can understand. I really loved this course!

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This was my first programming course and it helped me understand the basics. The teachers did an excellent job of explaining things at beginner level. I'm looking forward to their next course!

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This was a fantastic class. The instructors were thorough and interesting. Concepts were very clearly explained, and it gives a very good basis for learning how to program. Loved it!

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Excellent introductory course, great base for deep diving into programming. Slow paced, very concise, these guys did great job creating this course. Fully recommended. Both thumbs up.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents:
A great way to learn python at a slow and moderate pace for experienced programers that don't have a lot of free time to do so.

And a great way to how to program for complete novices.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents:
A good introduction. I liked that there were quizzes built into the video lectures, it helped keep me focused.

Started the course as a rank beginner and learned a lot.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: The instructors had some great explanations and examples of concepts that I had previously had a difficult time understanding. This was a great introductory class.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Excellent beginner class. They really make an effort to provide a gentle introduction to programming -- yet still make the material challenging and interesting.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents:
Excellent class.

Read review of 2012-12-16 which starts with "jennifer and Paul are both World Class..." - I agree with all.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: An excellent beginner's class that taught sound fundamentals. This enabled me to take other classes with good basic knowledge in place.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Very good introductory class. I feel like I got a very good fundamental understanding of Python and enjoyed learning from Jennifer and Paul.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This class was good: it focused on very basic things and focused on good code writing style. It's useful if you are just starting out.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: This was a great beginning python class. I learned a great deal and I am looking forward to their next class Learn to Program II.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: this was an excellent class! Great for beginners as everything is explained in easy to understand detail.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: I highly recommend this for anyone beginning to program or the people who like to start programming in Python.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: A great introduction to programming in Python. My first experience of a MOOC and this course got me hooked.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents:
This class is good enough to learn fundamentals in programming with python.

worthy to spend your time

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: excellent introductory course, if you are looking to learn the baseics this is the course for you.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Would recommend it for kids age 10+ who start programming. Detailed instruction and great teachers!

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: I you have zero knowledge of programming, this course is a great place to get started.

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals
review_contents: Amazing class! I would recomend it for everbody who wants to start learning Python!!!

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals

title: Learn to Program: The Fundamentals

Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents:
I have tried a couple other MOOCS and gave up on them due to dis-organization. This course is well organized, and developed.

Plus, the biggest asset is Professor Mason. She is dynamic, engaging, passionate about her subject and truly wants to share her passion and knowledge. Even if you only have a passing interest in neuro - take this course! You will become engaged.

title: Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents: Challenging! A great overview of the nervous system. Professor Mason rocks. She is clear and extremely motivational. The best Mooc ever!

title: Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents: My first MOOC - Dr Peggy Mason is amazing! Loved it.

title: Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents: Great teacher! Very engaging lectures. I particularly enjoyed the laboratory sessions, with guided brain dissections (not advised to faint-of-stomach, though). Dr Mason is very good at communicating her passion for neurosciences. The course covers a variety of topics, not necessarily in a structured way but always with something interesting to learn.

title: Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents:
excellent course materials.

Amazingly clear and straightforward explanations of this complex subject, neurobiology.

I found attending and finishing this mooc a very rewarding experience!

I recommend for anyone with bases of biology and medicine otherwise it may be a struggle but give it a try!

title: Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents:
Excellent course, excellent teacher and excellent organization. The subject is really well developed and explained, with very interested additional resources.

Congratulations to Professor Peggy Mason.

title: Understanding the Brain: The Neurobiology of Everyday Life
review_contents: Some of the material was challenging, but the course was always interesting. You'll find yourself calling on the information in your day to day life. This course is definitely worth your while.

Introduction to Logic
review_contents: I dropped this class after 2 or 3 weeks despite having a 100% average on the assignments. The lectures were impossible to follow. I found myself reading a logic textbook to understand the material and do the homework. The book was far better than the video. After a few weeks, I decided I could use the textbook alone to learn logic and dropped the class.

title: Introduction to Logic
review_contents: logically understanding any human problem is become easy after doing this course. i suggest all my friends to go through this course.

title: Neural Networks for Machine Learning
review_contents: This is a hard class, it goes deep into the math behind neural networks and it goes deep into the design implementation of such network. It is also a unique opportunity to learn from someone who is a pioneer and one of the lead thinkers in the field of neural nets.

title: Neural Networks for Machine Learning
review_contents: If you interested in neural networks, this course may discover you a whole new world of possibilities. It is not easy, but is is definitely worth the effort.

title: Computational Neuroscience
review_contents: First Lecture Series was very good and interesting. If a "Cloud-Based" Lab was added to get real experience with Neurons and Modelling via Octave/Matlab code...it would really be an improvement over existing educational programs.

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: This is an excellent class to really understand money and banking. Prof. Mehrling is an excellent teacher who looks past abstract Keynesian vs. monetarist thinking and gets to the core of how banking really works. That being said, understand that this is not a casual "survey" course; if you're going to get the most out of the class, you have to work with the material.

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: The best MOOC i had over 27. Excellent way to explain the crisis of actual economic models, and proposes a new approach through the money view. A sure candidate for nobel Prize i few years....Dont miss it

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: This is the most interesting and well prepared MOOC course I ever took before. I took a half dozen of classes so far in the field of Finance, Economics and English language, but this course stands above all. Thank you Professor.

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: A beautifully crafted course. It offers a different-old-new way to see the money market and the work of the central bank. The lessons are clear and at the end you just would like him to go on.

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: Really great course, great profesor. I studied economics and this course was great for me since we get a different, more realistic view of the money market and the banking sector.

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: Extremely interesting, i would recommend also Part II. Very clear explanations, and thougthful readings.

title: Economics of Money and Banking, Part One
review_contents: Very good to understand how money works in contemporary banking system.

review_contents: Stunning course with a high pedagogic motivation and a practical orientation which is very much appreciated. I come from a non-physics background and the maths and programming were challenging at the beginning but ended up wanting MORE videos about how to calculate manifolds in practice and more homework on Lyapunov exponents etc. For me it was just GREAT!

title: Nonlinear Dynamics: Mathematical and Computational Approaches
review_contents: Loved the course. Great introduction to the math behind several concepts that were, in turn, hinted at in the Introduction to Complexity course on Complexity Explorer. I agree with other reviewers that are interested in more in-depth courses or tutorials that delve into more examples on how to apply these concepts, rather than simply understand them.

title: Nonlinear Dynamics: Mathematical and Computational Approaches
review_contents: Exceptionally well taught, well organized, very good balance between theory and practice. The programming assignments were fun and motivating. It would be nice to have in the future a second, "advanced", session.

title: Nonlinear Dynamics: Mathematical and Computational Approaches
review_contents: Very good and well taught. The quizs are informative as well. Many examples were given to make learning easier. I highly recommend.

review_contents: Very good and worth doing but hard work. My education has been in history - reading texts from strange times and cultures and weighing half-formed, messy evidence. This was technical; it has real world application but, as with any course in logic, do not expect human color. I will give it another, effortful try at a later time.

title: Introduction to Mathematical Thinking
review_contents: I enjoyed this course, I am glad I took it. The Professor was very enthusiastic, and the lectures were well done. All the course material was available on time. The material does not lend itself as well to the online format as say the programming courses. I thought the course was well done in spite of that. I think more peer review on the assignments instead of just the final would help.

title: Introduction to Mathematical Thinking
review_contents: I can feel that the professor devoted a lot into this MOOC, and the evaluation rubric is somewhat interesting. Nevertheless, mathematics is indeed a bit dull, and it is not easy to hold on to the last...

title: Introduction to Mathematical Thinking
review_contents: Tough, fun and rewarding. Prof Devlin is an excellent and enthusiastic teacher.

title: Aboriginal Worldviews and Education
review_contents: I am sad this course will not be offered anymore, It was my first one. Learnt so much. The content was very thought provoking and was helpful in my teaching.

title: Introduction to Psychology
review_contents: It's a great intro to psychology, it covers a broad range of sub-types and gives you a good grasp on psychology as a whole.

review_contents: This is a fascinating course which is clearly presented by university lectures from various disciplines, and which involves practical tasks as well as the lectures and written texts. title: Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World
review_contents: A well-delivered and thorough introduction to the subject of complex systems and their relevance to our world. The lectures and accompanying notes were of very high quality. I would highly recommend this course to anyone even remotely interested in the subject matter.

title: Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World

It gave deep insights into how and why the Financial crisis happened .

It covered risk, uncertainty, networks, City development, etc.etc

title: Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World
review_contents: The course was a clear introduction to the principles of complexity. The presentation style made learning easy, and the lecturers clearly explained the different concepts. It was a good use of six weeks.

title: Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World
review_contents: An excellent course of a very fascinating subject. There are many teachers each offering a unique perspective. I liked the definitions provided on the various concepts and the part on leadership and entrepreneurship. Excellent and much needed advice.

title: Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World

title: GG101x: The Science of Happiness
review_contents: I loved this course. Lots of common sense, and self evident truths, but conveyed in a fresh, affirming way. I feel happy just thinking about it. Thanks to the teachers.

title: QM101.1x: Statistics for Business ? I
review_contents: I learned a lot of Excel and basic statistics from this course. The weekly assignments were practical, emphasizing learning-by-doing technique that helps student remember the concepts and Excel functions.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: It has been great to participate in this class and has expanded my boundaries poetically to a great extent. I think this has been a terrific learning experience and believe there is more to gain from this class. So much so in fact, that I am planning to take it a third time. Can you think of a course you would have considered doing that with during either your graduate or undergraduate years?

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Al Filreis and his sparklingly bright TAs have made poetry accessible, delightful and fun. The staff is relentlessly caring, thoughtful and inquisitive. Professor Al is a master moderator, bringing out the best thinking in TAs, poets and students alike. How they manage to make a community of 34,000+ people feel like a small group is mind-blowing. Bravo, UPenn, for sharing Al with the world.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This is a superb class for someone like me, fairly new to poetry. The videos have excellent discussion among people who are a mix of adults and students. They are fun, informative and educative. The FB community is very alive. What I like most is the involvement of the MODPO coordinator and his TAs in the FB community making it very personalised. I love and am coming back next year...

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Be aware this is a truly inspirational and life-changing course ? I have even travelled from the UK to attend some of the live webcasts in Philadelphia! As well as learning so much about American poetry, I feel part of a world community of people inspired to discuss complex issues together. A wonderful, wonderful example of truly collaborative learning led by some amazing teachers.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I can describe it in two words: life changing. I never completed university. Always felt like I was somehow lessened because of that. Turns out I do have a brain and it's functioning quite well, thank you, and from time to time I have something to say that other people like to hear. Al's nurturing enthusiasm (to a classroom of over 30,000 people!) is nothing short of amazing.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents:
This class is extraordinary, I am learning how to interpret and enjoy poems that I had never been exposed to before.

The videos are instructive, and the format (with the TAs around the table, all participating) makes it fun and engaging. I especially like been able to ask questions during "office hours"! I will take this course again next time it is offered.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents:
This highly participative and enthusiastically conducted class is a model for how online courses should be run. The class uses the entire gamut of online tools, from videos to online forums to live webcasts. The videos are not lectures, but rather close-reading discussions between the professor and a group of dedicated and intelligent students.

Highly recommended.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Hi, I participated in two time-overlapping MOOCs this fall. They perfectly complemented one another. One through Coursera and the other througth NovoEd. Poetry plus fiction. Both courses were rich with interesting material, but more importantly: kind people from all over the world. http://www.alonnashaw.com/2015/11/shockwaves-of-learning-online-classes.html

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This was a truly wonderful experience of both poetry and community. Professor Al Filreis and his TAs are deeply engaged and involved in the forum discussions, and are passionate about modern poetry. Peer review, instead of a score, involves commentary and continued discussion. I strongly recommend this class to anyone with an interest in poetry.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents:
ModPo is a unique experience. I've never known before such a wonderful encouraging learning community. It makes you more feel to be part of a process and a big team than some of face-to-face-courses I participated in.

The material and structure makes it very easy to find a way into the topic(s) and it is simply great - every turn again.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Al Filreis is superb at generating student interest, and very responsive in discussion forums. However his choice of poems is biased toward the life-denying rather than life-affirming -- he ignores too many of the great poems of the past century and focuses too much on the peripheral, especially the postmodern and experimental.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This is an amazing class, rich in resources and richer still in community. The heart of the class is the interactive discussions that occur 24-7 on the course forums, which create a marketplace of ideas. This interactivity is unique among the MOOCs I have seen and has provided one of the best learning experiences I have ever had.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Best course I've done for years, including paid ones. Lovely inclusive teaching method that makes you feel part of the group, loads of resources free online, great community spirit. Many on the course feel it has not only increased their understanding of poetry and of modernism, but changed their lives for the better

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I have paid for a number online courses and this has been of a better standard than most of those! The videos have been engaging and the assignments interesting. I came to the course with no knowledge of modern American poetry and have learned a lot about the subject, especially in relation to modern art.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Outstanding class! ModPo staff and instructor Al Filreis make the asynchronous communication seem almost synchronous through responsiveness and office hours. The pace is quick but manageable for most. This course covers a lot of ground, but does it in a very fun, social, and interactive way. Strongly recommended!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I took ModPo 1, but not ModPo 2 due to time constraints. ModPo gives a grounded but not dumbed-down approach to understanding the subtleties, nuances, depths and playfulness of poetry using an intelligent but informal approach. And THIS also benefited one of my red hens. Thank you, Al and TAs and classmates!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: ModPo is one of the most enriching learning doors I've ever opened. The level of energy, dedication, and communication in this class, from both staff and participants, is inspiring, as are the new ways of seeing that anyone in this course will experience! ModPo has set the bar for MOOCs for me.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I completed the course last year and am taking it again now for a second time. I was a poetry newbie a year ago and had my life transformed by this course. Not only do I love and better understand poetry, but I have connected with a wonderful community of fellow mod-poers. I highly recommend.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Gave me a brand new approach to poetry (the close reading), exposed me to poets I'd never read before, and allowed be to discuss it all with a world-wide community of like-minded people. Al Filreis and the TAs at Kelly Writers House kept things lively. I plan to do this again next year.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Super class. I have a 1st Class Honours in English Literature and an MA (with distinction), but this class has been a real mind opener, and a delight to take. Also, as a poet, I've found it so stimulating. I'd highly recommend it to anyone with a genuine interest in poetry or language.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This is my fourth year taking ModPo, and each year it feels fresh, deeper, and more poets to study. The first year I earned a certificate, but now I keep going back to push further into more serious studies of new and traditional American poets. Love every minute! Mary Manning Whitaker

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This class taught me how to analyze poetry. The community of learners is very interactive and engaging. There were live webcasts and/or audio messages several times a week. We were able to interact with our professor via telephone, Twitter, and by using the forums and Facebook.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I've taken several online courses and this is by far the best . It is well run. The teacher and the TAs are very knowledgeable about the subject. This course is for anyone no matter what your educational level. It makes you want to keep exploring on your own about the subject.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This class was fantastic. The videos feature a collaborative close reading between Al and his TAs, modelling the deep and thoughtful study of poetry that they want students to learn. Al and the TAs are deeply involved in the forums, offering help, advice, counsel and comfort.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Amazing experience with Al and his wonderful TA's..they become your other family. In 10 weeks, you will learn so much about poetry & become hooked. I had never read poetry before this class..never knew how to approach it..now I am hooked & plan to continue forever!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: If you have even the slightest interest in poetry this will be a rewarding experience. You will come away not only a stronger reader of poetry but a stronger reader. The level of staff participation will astonish you. Something valuable is being given away free!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents:
I can feel my brain expanding

Things I thought weren't poetry now sing to me

How can one find so much love and caring in a class of 34,000?

More up close and personal than classes I have taken in person with 20 people.

I have found a new home.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This class is unlike others. It is actually "taught" via a roundtable discussion and close reading of contemporary poems. You can take the course over again and learn something new each time. The best of the Coursera courses.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry is more than an online course, more than a MOOC, more than a learning experience - It is community. My community now spans the globe with friends in poetry, infinite possibility wherein I now dwell.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This is the MOOC in which I have been the most engaged. The course empowers students to think about and discuss challenging and interesting work. The evidence is in the volume and quality of the student forums. This is an amazing course.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I got a taste and initiation to this great course in 2014. . I am coming back for ModPo 2015 for seconds and savoring it this time with much gusto. Best MOOC I have ever participated in and I have taken many of them. I highly recommend it.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Do not let the word Poetry put you off taking this class. This course will teach you how to read and think. It is the most valuable course that I have ever experienced. The more I put into this course the more I got out of it.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Fantastic.. engaging, perplexing, thought-provoking, and with such support from the teaching staff and participants. I love this class. And I've taken about six coursera courses.. this rates among one of the best. Thanks Al et al!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Al Filreis is an amazing, engaging, and dynamic instructor, and this class has been fascinating from the very first week. If you're at all interested in the cutting edge of modern writing, this course is one not to be missed...

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This is my second turn in ModPo and I am again deeply convinced and impressed by the whole concept and the dedication Al Filreis and the TA's show. It was my first experience with an MOOC and I couldn't have made a better choice.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: ModPo blew away all my expectations! I can't say enough good things about the course, Prof. Al Filreis, the TAs, and everyone involved. It's been an enlightening, fun experience, and I highly recommend it!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Life changing class...humor, intelligence, poignancy...every week. This class is not to be missed (but WILL be very missed by all attendees when it's over.) I'm a ModPo-er for life. Thank-you Al Filreis and Team!

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents:
No question ....one of the best online courses available. Al and his very able team illuminate the most difficult of poems.

A joy to be in the company of the poets, the team and the students.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: This the best of the several MOOC I have taken. It is challenging and engaging. The forums are very active and enriching. It is life-changing. Everyone can benefit from an enjoy this course

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: Its just the most amazing experience, i would not have believed this was possible on a MOOC format , but it really is an incredibly positive learning experience. Try it and see !

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)
review_contents: I was part of the first class. The experience has remained an enriching highlight--including friends. Be prepared to be stimulated, stretched and awakened in the night.

title: Modern & Contemporary American Poetry (¡°ModPo¡±)

title: Introduction to Cyber Security
review_contents:
This course is useful if you have little to no knowledge on how to protect yourself. Content and recommendations are familiar to anyone who browse a bit too much internet. Course forum does suggest it's useful for people who weren't brought up with computers, i.e. older generations.

My actual rating: older generation - 4/5, everyone else - 1/5

title: Religion and Conflict
review_contents: It's very interesting and challenging! If fusion of religion, politics, and history is your forte, then you better take this course.

title: Religion and Conflict
review_contents: This is a great course with very rich material - theoretic, historical and contemporary - and lively exchanges with fellow students!

title: Religion and Conflict
review_contents: Leads you on a step by step review of the subject, the course is concise but yet does not seem as if it is lacking any information.

title: Blended Learning Essentials: Embedding Practice
review_contents: This course provides a thorough introduction to the issues surrounding embedding Blended Learning including learning analytics, cost and effective change management. It provides an opportunity to discuss approaches with other professionals and introduces some useful tools and research.

title: Cluster Analysis in Data Mining
review_contents: I thought the class was good for someone who already knows how to apply clustering analysis to data. I have been using different clustering algorithms in the past, this class gave me a greater overview of the other clustering methods that existed that I hadn't been exposed to. I do not recommend this for someone who is new to the concept/application of clustering.

review_contents: This was my first MOOC experience, and to date the best one. I enjoyed the lessons, and the support and the knowledge was greatly rewarding! I could see myself specializing in this at a later stage in my career; it was a great intro into the field.

title: Introduction to Complexity
review_contents: Clear, interesting and an excellent introduction to a variety of topics within the realm of complexity. Excellent course for those who have heard about complexity are are looking for an accessible yet sound introduction to the topic.

title: Introduction to Complexity

title: Introduction to Complexity
review_contents: Really amazing course. Melanie did a great job in explaining the basic concepts of complexity. Each lecture unravels its own universe and in the end they all came together.

title: Introduction to Complexity
review_contents: Loved it so much I took it twice. Very grateful to finally have the opportunity to study complexity theory thru SFI. Been studying it informally for 20 years.

title: Introduction to Complexity
review_contents:
A great course, great lectures, great materials. A lot of basis theory as a base for future studies.

title: Introduction to Complexity
review_contents: I took this course in its live version at University of New Mexico in Albuquerque. Melanie is a great teacher and has a gift for explaining complex principals in a simple and easy to understand way. The course is a great way to get a start in understanding Complex Adaptive Systems and covers the landscape of practical application areas very well.

review_contents: This has been a long course that is finally coming to an end. I started it with no knowledge of Shelley and no expectations. Within days I was hooked. The amount of work that has been put in by Eric and his team, the constant personal support and the heop of other particopants have created not only a course but also a community. Simply wonderful.

title: The Great Poem Series: Unbinding Prometheus
review_contents: Shelley's Prometheus Unbound has been a unique experience for study of the period, the poet and the Romantics in early 19th century. There was top quality seminars and discussions from outstanding experts, poets and academics. There was opportunity to study thoroughy. The posts were inspiring and deeply thoughtful. A great deal of work went in by all. A rich experience I recommend.

title: The Great Poem Series: Unbinding Prometheus
review_contents:
A great course which helped me think in different ways about a text (and a tale) that I did not know well. The assignments were intriguing, and I enjoyed the opportunity to be creative around the text (and beyond). While I was unable to finish because of professional commitments, I would love to finish the course at another time.

~Kerry Mohnike

title: The Great Poem Series: Unbinding Prometheus
review_contents: I had tried to read Shelley's Prometheus Unbound more than once prior to this course but always found myself lost and frustrated. Taking this course was crucial to being able to really approach this amazing piece of art, appreciate it, and learn from it. This course is really a great gift to those who appreciate English literature.

title: The Great Poem Series: Unbinding Prometheus
review_contents: This is such an outstanding course, I hesitate to even call it a course, its really a lifestyle. The level and depth of the materials goes far and beyond most other MOOCs that I've taken, and I'm so glad that it will be repeated because I simply didn't budget enough time for all of the materials and can't wait to do it again.

title: The Great Poem Series: Unbinding Prometheus
review_contents: Really impressive course on a difficult dramatic poem. Eric has clearly put a huge amount of thought and effort into putting this together. I discovered it late so I've had to dash through parts of it. I very much look forward to doing a future iteration in more detail.

title: The Great Poem Series: Unbinding Prometheus
review_contents: Prometheus Course was wonderful. A great community of people to discuss the poems with and learn new things. Eric is a wonderful professor and always in the discussion forums and available to help! It's an amazing class. I'll be there next year when it starts again.

title: Model Thinking
review_contents:
This was my first MOOC and it hooked me in a big way. Professor Page keeps it fresh, interesting, and challanging throught the course. I found out that I was using models for most of my life without knowing it. He absolutly made me better at it (the more models the better, I got it Professor).

I never anticipated that the experience would be so rewarding.

title: Model Thinking
review_contents: Great course. It opened my mind to many new ideas that I didn't knew existed. The topics are so varied that unfortunately the contents don't have much depth, but Dr. Page teaches you just enough for you to start learning on your own about whatever topic picked your interest. Highly recommended!

title: Model Thinking
review_contents: A broad introduction to a diverse collection of useful models for thinking about the world. You will need a bit of algebra, but the course is not math-intensive. Great lectures. Over and over, I found myself saying "That's fascinating!" One of my favorites

title: Model Thinking
review_contents: I took the class last year. It's one of the best courses that I have done so far. Prof. Scott covers political, economical, business , and many other models. It's amazing how different fields are connected.

title: Model Thinking

title: Model Thinking

title: Think101x: The Science of Everyday Thinking
review_contents: This was my first MOOC and I was blown away by the presentation by the course instructors. This course compels us to rethink about our own thinking, why we do things that we do and how can we improve our thinking and thus enhance our decision making and quality of life. I would strongly recommend everyone to do this course.

title: Think101x: The Science of Everyday Thinking
review_contents: This course was seriously one of the best I have taken. Explaining concepts through dialogue and interviews with many different (also high-calibre) thinkers made this course really worthwhile. Would recommend it to anyone.

title: Think101x: The Science of Everyday Thinking
Think101x: The Science of Everyday Thinking
review_contents: I loved this course. It was my first MOOC. The lectures were done in a dialogue style, I found them easy to listen to. The content is very interesting, but also founded in the scientific methods. They were very pro-science, so that's something you should keep in mind.

title: Think101x: The Science of Everyday Thinking
review_contents: My first online course.I spent about 6hours per day and completed in 10days!!incredible!!I recommend it to everyone who wants to ameliorate their way of thinking

Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Really recommended! The instructor is brilliant while presenting every detail of the class. His explanations are clear and neat, and you definitely learn how to program on Python. What I really like about Udacity courses in general is that you are not constraint to schedules, you learn to your own pace, contents are updated, you learn a lot, and you can even get a certificate.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: This was my first programming course of any kind. I thought the pace and the topics were well thought out and covered many programming topics in a serious way. The coding interface works well and the forums were very friendly and helpful. I would highly recommend this course!

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents:
Although building a search engine using Python is the project to complete by the end of the course, the main outcome is to learn general programming concepts.

This is basically what final exam is testing, but don't worry, it's impossible not to learn well as the course has many quizzes and exercises.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: I really loved this class. It is self paced, very well organized, with lots of exercises. I highly recommend it to everyone new to programming,, because it starts from the scratch. But as with all self-paced courses, you have to apply a bit of a discipline in order to finish it.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Ability to take it at my own pace is very important to me. Great course design, informative lectures, meaningful and consistent material. This is a complete package, no additional resources needed to complete the course requirements.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Great class for beginners, although it doesn't delve much into Class definitions or other object-oriented aspects. All assignments are very helpful, and a very complex working product is constructed at the end, which in hindsight is quite impressive.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents:
Excellent introduction to Python for beginners and those new to python. He teaches some great tools including recursion with cacheing. It was my first programming course and I thoroughly enjoyed it.

He is a great teacher.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Prof. Evans introduces Python is a clear and thoughtful way; the end result is a function search engine. Highly recommended for anyone wishing to learn to program or requiring a quick introduction to the language.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Important course for CS students. It starts from the basic such as data types to functions, lists, dictionaries , indexes, and algorithms. Search engine is used as the example of application, but assignment have more exercises.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Great course. Highly recommend to beginners. Give it a try if you want to learn computer science. Nice to be able to watch the videos and pause them where you need to.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Very solid class. Well worth the effort. David Evans is able to explain ideas very well. The frequent quizzes are helpful. The problem set are well constructed.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: The best class i join it ever. Prof. David Evans really worked hard to make all information and materials in this course simple as possible.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents:
This was an excellent introduction to python as well as a look into how search engines work.

Excellent class

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: Great intro to programming course where by the end you have actually built something substantial.

title: Intro to Computer Science
review_contents: This is a very informative course. I'm glad I decided to take this course. The instruction was clear and concise.

title: DB: Introduction to Databases
review_contents: I liked the course as it allowed me to cover a lot of new things, and go deep in the topics I was interested in. The lectures were clear and engaging, and the tasks were though challenging but interesting. I think it is a really good course, as it's leading you smoothly through the materials and motivating to accomplish most you can.

title: Competitive Strategy
review_contents: A nice, simple yet well-thought out introduction to competitive strategy provided by Prof Kretschmer, and I am now mid-way through his second course Advanced Competitive Strategy. This course is easy to follow even for a non-specialist, but introduces the concepts in a very broad manner allowing the knowledge to be applied across a wide range of situations.

title: Competitive Strategy
review_contents: Absolutely phenomenal course, the instructor goes through the material in a very easy to understand way, is engaging, and the subject matter is presented with practical and real-world examples to support the theory!

6.002.1x: Circuits and Electronics 1: Basic Circuit Analysis
review_contents: This is an excellent course to get you started in electronics. The textbook is very helpful. It gives you confidence when reviewing schematics and solving for voltages and currents. I would recommend this course to any student that wants to be an electrical engineer.

title: 6.002.1x: Circuits and Electronics 1: Basic Circuit Analysis
review_contents:
Really excellent courses, all three of them. Never banal, full of insights. It was really a pleasure to work ('cause you have to work) with such a good professor, helpful assistants and fellow students. I've learned a lot, much more than I initially expected.

Fabio

title: 6.002.1x: Circuits and Electronics 1: Basic Circuit Analysis

This is a very good lesson with a good balance between concepts, engineering point of view and practical applications.

Thank you very much for that.

Highly recommended class!

title: MedStats: Statistics in Medicine
review_contents: Prof. Sainani is the best! You will have to work at it, but the material will really hold you in good stead for future use and advanced classes.

title: How to Build a Startup
review_contents: A truly inspiring course: well paced, feels participative, perfectly designed learning for a MOOC platform. Made me flip my thinking, really forced me into action, to 'get out of the building ' and test and pivot the idea. Loved it.

title: How to Build a Startup
review_contents: I loved this course. It's bright, high tech, and practical. Recommend this course for business students as well as business professionals.

title: How to Build a Startup
review_contents: Innovative delivery and course design. The content is excellent and a "must have" for any entrepreneur. This can save you hundreds of hours of wasted time and potentially save you thousands of dollars, and perhaps save your start up. Follow me at http://twitter.com/audaciousinnov8

title: How to Build a Startup

title: Web Development
review_contents: The video lectures are very well made and quizzes help reinforce the material without being too difficult. The class covers a wide range of topics including HTTP requests, basic HTML, getting user input, databases, user authentication, cookies, caching, scaling and APIs. It touches on CSS very briefly and barely mentions JavaScript, so look elsewhere if you are interested in front-end development.

title: Web Development
review_contents:
Fun class, You will have built your own blog and wiki by the end on google app engine. You will learn how to make logins and cookies and keep a database of users secure.

I would recommend learning a bit of HTML and CSS first as you will want to make your site look pretty and he will only teach the very basics you need to get your site up.

title: Web Development
review_contents: Great course for those just moving into the intermediate level of programming. I finished wishing it had more but looking back you really do accomplish quite a lot. This course really could use a unit on AJAX and the client-side JavaScript frameworks (at least touching on them).

title: Web Development
review_contents: Absolutely amazing course. If you know some Python (up through at least Object Oriented programming), you can go from knowing 0 about web development to creating your own web apps from scratch!

title: Web Development
review_contents: Very informative class and i strongly suggest this course for all developers

title: Web Development
review_contents: Great course. Some material is old because this course is created several years ago. However 90 percent of the material is latest and the foundation is great. It is an alternative choice if you don't want to spend more time to take full-stack nanodegree or you have much experience in application development and self studying by official documents.

title: Web Development
review_contents: Awesome instructor. A must learn course. Learned a lot to start with web development, at the end real issues of scaling are touched.

title: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
review_contents: I watched these lectures on MIT's OCW as a supplement to a circuits and devices course at Penn State University -- University Park (EE 210). These lectures helped reinforce (and, at times, clarify) the most important concepts in my course. Highly recommended.

title: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
review_contents: Of the 5 courses I've taken on edx and coursera, this was the Gold Standard. Everything was done right. The lectures were exceptional with annotated and clean lecture slides. The homework, exams, and labs are both challenging and instructive. Course administration was well managed. (Took spring 2012)

title: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
review_contents: Wow! What an amazing effort. I am a university professor, taking this course to learn about MOOCs. I cannot express how much I admire Prof. Agarwal and his team for putting this superb course together and offering it for free to the world.

title: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
review_contents: This course is the one I currently rank above all the other online courses I have taken. The lectures were clear and interesting. The problem sets were the right difficulty and very insightful. Some work does need to be done on the homework page layout and input of formulas. They may have fixed that in the current iteration (I took the initial March-June 2012 class). Excellent course.

title: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
review_contents: Brilliant course, brilliant lecturer. Difficult concepts were broken down into manageable portions. I cannot recommend it more. The pace was right and contents were right too.

title: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
review_contents: One of my first MOOCs! Fast paced, difficult course that is very rewarding if you manage to get through it. The interactive labs were great!

title: DCO042 - Python For Informatics
review_contents: I've tried (and failed) to learn basic programming in the past. This course was accessible, easy to follow and fun. The lectures and exercises demystify Python and programming in general. Plus Chuck is one of the most entertaining lecturers I've ever had. There were a lot of times when I laughed out loud. Not something I would've expected from a course on programming. Highly recommended.

title: DCO042 - Python For Informatics
review_contents:
I have done programming before but that was 6 years ago. His stuff was a amazing way to get back into it. His book and the course together are a great way to dive into understanding programming.

I would recommend this to anyone and everyone looking to learn programming or refresh on it.

title: DCO042 - Python For Informatics
review_contents: Dr. Chuck did a really beautiful job with this MOOC I highly recommend this course for absolute beginners. You will learn the basics of programming and will allow you to take more challenging courses.

title: DCO042 - Python For Informatics
