title: Archaeology's Dirty Little Secrets
review_contents: One of the best run MOOCs i've encounted, and i've taken over 15 of them. The prof. is smart and full of enthusiasm. The assignments are fun to do plus you get to pick which ones to do each week. The discussion boards were very active.

title: Archaeology's Dirty Little Secrets
review_contents: I have taken many MOOCs and this is the best one! The professor is passionate about archaeology and you can tell by the way the class is taught.

title: Stat2.1X: Introduction to Statistics: Descriptive Statistics
review_contents:
The professor's video presentations are excellent. She mixes a casual humor with an astonishing ability to communicate complex ideas and concepts clearly and articulately.

The online textbook, with its statistics calculators, is an excellent resource and great benefit of the course.

title: Stat2.1X: Introduction to Statistics: Descriptive Statistics
review_contents:
Excellent and very well organised course for an intro to stats. There is no software package needed to learn for the completion of the assignments and tests. Everything is provided and explained thoroughly.

Highly recommended.

title: Stat2.1X: Introduction to Statistics: Descriptive Statistics
review_contents: Great teacher, focus on understanding of the subject and not on a bunch of formulas.

title: Stat2.1X: Introduction to Statistics: Descriptive Statistics
review_contents: #NAME?

title: Stat2.1X: Introduction to Statistics: Descriptive Statistics
review_contents: It's an excellent course for a beginner in Statistics.

WALL STREET MOOC: Understanding Financial Markets
review_contents: This course has been interesting. You can gain some knowledge about financial instruments. it has very good synthesized reading and it gives mozilla badges.

title: Practical Ethics
review_contents:
Eye-opening course.

Dr. Singer does a very good job in bringing up different points of view of several topics, and how to critically create your own ethic conduct out of reasoning, avoiding the pitfalls of socially-acquired biases.

A Look at Nuclear Science and Technology
review_contents: A balanced into to nuclear energy. It sounds more intimidating than it turned out to be! Lecturer was engaging

title: A Look at Nuclear Science and Technology
review_contents: It was my first MOOC, and my first experience was really good. Perhaps that's why I am continuing to participate in more MOOCs.

title: A Look at Nuclear Science and Technology
La visione del mondo della Relativit? e della Meccanica Quantistica
review_contents: Great cours held by Professor Carlo Cosmelli (Departiment of physics) of university La Sapienza in Rome. Very interesting and clear.

title: 001x: Medicinal Chemistry: The Molecular Basis of Drug Discovery
review_contents: This was a fantastic course. The lectures were clear and engaging and I came to love the subject. This is so far the best MOOC I have taken!

Highly recommended!

review_contents:
I am a college prof and teach online myself, so I was especially impressed with the set up and video production quality.

My only issue is that the title of the course itself does not really do justice to talking others into the course. This is a course I can literally recommend to anyone! Hard to imagine anyone not finding this fascinating, regardless of their profession or goals.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This was a very interesting class. When I would tell my friends the name of the course, they would roll their eyes and question why I would take the class, however once I would tell them about the class material, they wanted to know if it was too late to join in.

Dr. Ariely does a great job presenting the material and the filming and extras interjected into the course are top notch.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
One of the best on line courses I have ever found. Very nice video lectures and great reading materials.

It's not exactly a beginners course, although it doesn't have any pre requisites. May be a little hard for non native English speakers as the readings include academic papers and you have to write a (short) essay. Some people complained on the peer review method to grade the essays

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great course! This course applies to everyday life situations at work and beyond. I found it both fun and useful. I started it out of curiosity but ended up regretting I didn't do the quizzes from the beginning. The reading is not too time consuming... The only thing I could possibly be unhappy about is the professor¡¯s opinion of cats, but that¡¯s freedom of speech for you :)

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This class was not for beginners. It had a longer time commitment mostly due to the extensive academic readings. This class had only 1 certificate track compared to other Coursera classes that ofter 3 certificate tracks.

This class also had a high pass rate of 85%. Lastly, the final was a "closed book" test which seemed useless since there were admitted cheaters.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Fantastic experience. Dr. Ariely is a great lecturer and he and his assistants did an excellent job in putting together an enjoyable and educational experience. The material was fascinating, the readings were relevant (if at times quite technical) and the videos were easy to follow and understand. This was my first Coursera course and it has certainly set a very high standard.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: i had joined this class to have an experience about behavior,although i had read all 3 books of dan ariely which were really good ,this class was an perfect amalgm of all theories related to human behavior.the assignments were also really nice ,at times they were really nerve breaking,overall i am really satisfied with this class and what i have learnt for past 8 weeks.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
I've enrolled in this course twice now, bought Dan's books and installed his tablet app. This is a fascinating and very well taught, engaging course. You'll see human behaviour in a whole new light!

To cover everything and gain the distinction you'll have to not only watch the videos but do a lot of reading, some of which is quite dense. It's not a fluffy course.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
amazing course based on scientific experiment on behavior. a bunch of humor to address serios subjects.

high quality video, well structured and capable to adjust to your need from introduction up to advanced..

No pre-requisite required.

for non-english, level C1-C2 or a strong curiosity to digg on communication level (from slang to high level)

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Ariel is a great professor and the course was excellent. It was interactive and full of examples. What I like most was that there were quizzes and final questions for all the lessons, which collaborated with the focus on the course (i.e. against procrastinaton). I really reccommend the course and for sure if there will be a part II,I will take it.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great class, lot's of information presented in a way conducive to retaining the information provided. It takes time and attention each and every week to complete this course with success. Video lectures are superbly done and the professor very knowledgeable in the subject. Overall a perfect class to learn why we do or do not make the choices we make

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: A well designed, brilliantly presented and delivered course with excellent video, reading and online resources. A safe, supportive and encouraging online learning community throughout, underpinned by Dan and his Team's commitment to their students' successful learning of complex material in a fun and memorable experience. Free, yet Priceless!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This is an excellent class. The course material relates to behavioral economics and psychology and is very interesting. Professor Dan Ariely's presentation style is entetaining and engaging. The workload for the course was low for me. I found the quizzes and exams relatively easy.

I would recommend any courses offered by Dan Ariely.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Loved it! Lots of practical information and tips to apply to daily life and my business.

Loved the format. It was easy to stay engaged in the class. I looked forward to the lectures.

Loved it enough to take it again in the future. The concepts were so new to my way of thinking I know I can garner even more learning from this class!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Truly amazing and helpful class! You get insights for your everyday life, for the workplace and so on! It gets you closer to understand our behavior under some specific circunstances! A "must take" course! Plus, the material is really good as they have lots of experience in this course and have built a real learning community

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: It's a great course. It's hard work even if you're only watching the lectures. There's a lot of testing (quizzes, popup questions and so forth)--that can be annoying sometimes. Although I loved the content, I was a bit overwhelmed by the sheer breadth of it. There's a lot to understand and memorize. At any rate, I recommended it for sure!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Videos were a lot of fun. Even the quizzes had a sense of humour. Dan obviously put a lot of thought into each video, and the graphics/animations/videos were professionally done. I would love to be able to take a face-to-face course with this professor. I have read his books as a result of this course, and look forward to his next one.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This is a fantastic course. I would unreservedly recommend this course to any one curious about human nature and wants to learn the nuances of why people behave the way they do. It clarifies your mind about so many things in day-to-day life that it is applicable in your personal situations as well. I enjoyed it and I benefitted from it.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Really well explained concepts and theories, everything bases on experiments performed. Indeed, you don't need a background in economics to understand the course, it is easy for everyone to learn and helps you rethink about your everyday choices (financial and otherwise). I would say it is very practical and easy to apply to your daily life.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Excellent class! It was 90% entertainment and 10% work. Interesting content, great use of visuals and technology, excellent style of delivering video lectures. Every concept is illustrated by examples and many of those are truly entertaining.

Thanks a lot to the whole team and I hope you will the financing for the 2nd course on this!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great course, educational, informative, FUNNY. You will learn and laugh at the same time. Brilliantly done. Ariely also writes books, I highly recommend you get them as well. I've studied different areas of economics (behavioural, normative, neuro) and by far, behavioural makes a lot of sense. Highly recommended for everyone!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Loved the whole experience! Thanks so much, Dan for introducing this course- the very title caught the eye. Excellent content presented with great examples in tandem with Dan's endearing style of presenting combined with his contagious enthsiasm made this course my favourite so far.

Thanks!:-)

Sonali Nambiar

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Excelent course! Professor Dan Ariely is wonderful! Very comitted and still sweet and has a good humour.

The course helped me to decode my daily choices and see it from a different perspective.

I`m already missing professor Dan`s video lectures and hoping he will come back soon!

Vanessa from Brazil

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I really liked this course. While not perfect from a didactical perspective, it was a lot of fun. Dan Ariely was very engaged and experimented with lots of options for designing the course, although not all of them worked out. The teaching assistants were very helpful in the discussion forums. Thumbs up!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: EXCELLENT. Course topics are insightful and useful to everyday life, in the personal and/or professional sphere. Prof Ariely is a delightful lecturer. Quality execution on learning experience - great mix, pace & variety of content / quizzes / guests etc kept it engaging, accessible and flexible. A model MOOC.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Super course! It debunks the theory that Economics is a science. So far I just knew formula-based economics theories, that fail when test in the real life. This course is about alternatives. Dan observes how people actually act and why, offers interesting solutions, and demonstrates it in charismatic way:)

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Just wrapped up this class. It's hands down the best online class I've taken. So much care is put into the materials it's more a labor of love than an online class.

And it will change the way you live your life, for the better. What more could you ask for in exchange for a few hours of your time over 6 weeks?

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Excellent class, on which you can spend as little or as much time as you like. The video lectures take about an hour per week. There is enough reading material available to spend another ten hours if you are so inclined. Dan Ariely is a gifted speaker, who makes Behavioral Economics fun and easy to comprehend.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Essential principles for anyone to learn. A course that should be taken by all human beings who want to understand human behavior and who would like to free themselves from the bonds of irrational choices! I hope to take the course again when I can try for the distinction pathway...I started it too late.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Really good material, lots to learn for everyday life and corporate life too. Really interesting lectures, a well planned package successfully put together with a lot of effort, topped by the charismatic Dan Ariely himself. If all learning was dished out in this way - wouldn't it be wonderful...

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This was a great course ... I'm going to miss it (although I'll be happy to have some free time in my week now). I would take another class if Dr. Ariely designs it. I would be quite willing to take a for-payment, non-credit class (somewhere between free and Duke tuition would be nice - smile).

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: An Amazing course, very comprehensive and superbly presented, enriched with different guess presenters and complemented by reading the supports the video lectures. Great content, with Dan as an incredible communicator that reaches out to you with his passion and knowledge. Truly magnificent!!!!!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great Course - Nice structure and easy to follow. Plenty of information that can be applied to the real world. Dan's lectures are easy to follow and well pitched for anyone to follow. Support team are also on the ball, promptly replying to any questions and queries in a clear and professional manner.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: The best Coursera course I have taken so far. Very interesting lectures, lots of examples mostly from Dan Ariely's own studies, a professor with a good sense of humour, fair exams, a good team, top materials etc. A great experience, I hope this course and/ or a subsequent course will be offered again.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Even if combining my college studies with this course ultimately became very difficult, this might be one of the most interesting pieces of e-learning that you can find on the web. Dan Ariely offers a unique experience and great lessons on the fascinating discipline of Behavioral Economics.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Very informative and interesting, materials well presented. This course let you know a great deal more about yourself and others, you will also be able to apply what you learnt in your daily life.

Definitely recommend this course to everyone, especially if you are interested in psychology.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Great! The lectures were engaging, and I really liked the format--short chunks of lectures, reading and lecture quizzes (for the normal certificate, you just had to do the lecture quizzes and the final), and extra guest mini-lectures.

Really fun and useful topic. Highly recommended!!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Very nicely presented, behavioral economics with a touch of humor and applicable to day-to-day situations. Academic background research and experiments do back up what is presented online. Easy to enroll and to follow through, but requires work if desire is to master contents presented.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Everything about the course is perfect. For the first time I had fun while learning. The materials were easy to assimilate. The illustrations, demonstrations and method of teaching was quite engaging. The best part is that I have been able to apply what I learnt in my personal development.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I loved this class. The technical side worked and the material was interesting and relevant to every day life. Dr. Ariely is a wonderful lecturer who is clear, entertaining, genuine and makes the material come alive and be helpful to how you live your life. I strongly recommend it to all.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I found myself straying from class do to my ADD. So much information coming to me all at once and it made me feel intimidated and hard to retain all the information. I dropped out when it got closer to the writing assignment . I enjoyed what part I did participate in very much.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I constantly take a half dozen or so Coursera classes for pure enjoyment; not interested in certificates. I watch all lectures, read supplemental info and explore the discussion fora. This is one of the most informative and fascinating courses I've taken and I recommend it highly!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Excellent class with a very engaging professor. Weekly assignments are clearly assigned, with optional reading assignments and written assignments.

Plan on 4-6 hours per week if you want to get the most out of it.

Course material is very practical and quite interesting.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Excellent class. Very informative. Lectures are interesting and enjoyable to watch. This course stimulates me to observe and try to understand the behavior of myself and people around me in my daily life. I have learnt a lot. Thanks Dr Ariely and his team for creating this class.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This class was entertaining, thought provoking and changed the way I look at the world. Professor Ariely is amazing. I highly recommend this course to all who want to examine their own behavior and gain insights into how they can manage themselves and their lives more effectively.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This is a fabulous course if you work in a field where you make decisions that influence others. It is also wonderful if you want to know why you do things and how to improve your life. My work life, my personal life and my decisions will be better after taking this course.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great class! Very engaging and thoughtfully prepared. You can see how much work Dan Ariely and his team put into creating that course. Definitely the best organized MOOC I took so far! Hope other lectures will follow presenting their material in similarly fascinating way.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This is a great mental "stretch". It explores some of the irrational behaviors we all have, but maybe didn't know we had.

The instructor and team put a lot of thought and work into the class to make it a full and fun learning experience, and it shows.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
It was my second attempt to take this class. Last yea I started to listen to lectures, but unfortunately hadn't enough time to complete. So this year I tried again.

Professor Dan Ariely is fantastic lecturer! I enjoyed all lectures. He is doing a rely good job!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I had an amazing learning experience with this course. It was easy to understand. i am now applying my leanings in my daily life regularly. I feel happy that I am able to relate my learnings to my daily dealings with various problems of life. Very enriching course.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Incredibly entertaining and informative course. All subject matter was presented in a really enjoyable way, and was very easy to comprehend. The course is loaded with experimental information, and even chances to get involved yourself. I loved every minute of it.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
By far, the best MOOC I ever attended.

If you are intersted in the topic, this is great course for you. The class is very entertaining and you learn a lot through this course.

If you want to get the best out of this class, you need to reserve 7 hours per week.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Dan's passion for Behavioral Economics is highly electrifying and his teaching ability makes the passion equally contagious. Unfortunately I couldn't complete the program and earn a certificate. I am waiting to re-experience and relish the course once again!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: A brilliant course that exceeded my expectations in all respects and went even further in making me feel an active participant in an academic course as if I was sitting in Professor Ariely's class and interacting with everyone. Well done to everyone at Duke!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This is by far one of the best online classes I have ever taken. This course should be an example for how all online classes should be presented and taught. The material is interesting, the professor was engaging, the presentations were visually appealing.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I highly recommend everyone who's interested in knowing how we (human beings) do certain things, take certain decisions, what influences us, how it's irrational and how we can make changes in our actions and perceptions for making better decisions.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This class was really good. Very applicable to everyday life. It has good material and it uses current research. The Professor was really good, and the lectures and readings were very interesting.

I'd would most definitely recommend it.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Really a great class.

I learnt so many things in this class, about everyday life as well as corporate life.

The Professor is also very good at presenting the materials from his extensive work.

I would recommend this class to everybody.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great class, really, a lot of fun, interesting content, which you can directly apply in your everyday life, fun way of presenting it. Aside for the lectures, you have a bunch of academic articles recommended, plenty of research designs.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I thoroughly enjoyed this class. I wish I had had time to delve more deeply into the readings; instead I simply watched the videos and took the quizzes. For the small effort I put in, I learned a lot and now want to explore the topic more.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Very very good. Good course material, good supporting literature, excellent quizzes and essay style course work. In an ideal world I would want it to be longer and to go into more depth, but I suppose these guys have to earn a living somehow.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: I had a wonderful experience in this course. The lectures were interesting and not boring at all. Academic reading did get to you a bit. But then it wouldn't be complete experience without it. I hope to see more courses from Professor Ariely.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Dan Ariely provided an interesting and relevant overview of Behavioural Economics, in an enthusiastic and exciting way. The course was very very organised and run. Thanks to this course I am inspired to take other online courses from Coursera.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: The information in this class would be useful to anyone interested in how they -- and others -- spend their money, use their time, and speak. The course is easy to navigate and the instructor has, in my opinion, a great sense of humor.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: An excellent course. I recommend it to everyone. You'll be surprised how little you know about human decision making and other kinds of behavior. I've found out that the course is useful and applicable to real-life situations.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This was one of the most amazingly organised class that I have attended. Besides, the content was top rate, and the reading material painstakingly assembled to be informative and interesting.

Highly recommended for everyone!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Amazing course. IWhy people do what they do and why. Easy to watch and listen to, Dan Ariely is a brilliant lecturer and the material is interesting but easy to follow with plenty of extra content should you want it.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great course, with a lot of take away and useful information, also fun and challenging on an intellectual level. The right balance between common-sense and specialized information, just the thing that MOOCs should always be.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Dr. Ariely is a great lecturer and learning was really enjoyable end fun. Course indeed changed my consumers habits. Also very important, English is not my native language but I found no difficulties during learning process.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
It¢¥s very very precisely structured and profoundly presented and so watching and listening becomes great joy. Also much thanks to the whole team of Dan Ariely.

Would like to be part of the class for a third time.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: A wonderful course! Well presented video lectures with a touch of humour. It was never boring, the exaples and experiments are very relevant and can help to understand your decision in day-to day life. Loved this course!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Dan is an excellent lecturer who also obviously (together with his small team) put a lot of time and effort into this brilliant, entertaining and fascinating presentation of this intriguing and thought provoking material.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Absolutely fantastic class! I am so happy I had the chance to take it, and so thankful towards all the wonderful people that made it possible. Highly recommendable, even for someone not as keen on the topic as I am.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: It's a pity that my professors at the university didn't love their subjects as Mr. Ariely loves his one. I would surely recommend the course to my friends. I learned a lot of stuff that is useful for me in my everyday life.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great course - interesting, engaging, motivating. Cannot rate this course and Dan Ariely highly enough. Any future MOOCs I do will find it impossible to match this one. Congratulations to all concerned at Duke University.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great course, fascinating topic, learnt many interesting things about utilizing human weaknesses for good. Highly recommend this course to anyone who is in marketing, sales, psychology, and just to anyone!!!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: During six weeks you will get a clear overview of some very interesting behavioral eco topics. Due to the clear explanations and real-life examples it does not feel like studying but definitely stays in your mind.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
This is one of the best classes I ever had:

Lectures are fun, and help keeping the main points in your mind.

Has many supporting reading materials.

Has great office Hours videos on which one can participate.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Amazing course, the way to deliver the class was exceptional, and even though it is a virtual class, it is way better than some face 2 face classes.

Also compared to other courses online this is top of the line.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents:
Excellent course! Given in very accessible way so even people with no knowledge on the subject can enjoy it.

It was really entertaining :) and what is most important - it can help anybody in everyday life.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This class really opened my eyes to a lot of behaviors I have and/or see every day and why some of them happen even though rationally you would think they never would. Also, the teacher is amazing and hysterical!

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: Great course, really enjoyed the classes, reading Don't books and giving quizzes and exams. The course delivered exactly what was offered at the start - an excellent insight into our 'flawed'' decision making.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior
review_contents: This class was interesting, educational and very enjoyable. Dan Ariely is a very vibrant and wonderful speaker. He definitely draws you into the material. I would certainly take another class with him.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior

title: A Beginner's Guide to Irrational Behavior

Modeling (i.e linear regression, logistic regression etc.) are well explained by examples using R.

review_contents:

A must follow for anyone who wants to become a data scientist.

review_contents: Overall; outstanding. Well structured with good balance of video lecture, articles, quizes etc. Transcripts available to allow reading and listening simultaneously. Thoroughly recommended.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: I really enjoyed this course. It was new to me but linked to thoughts like "what makes this body/mind me?" Having finished, it is possible to download much of the material so it can be reviewed in the future after mulling over some of the ideas and insights. Thank you to all the team who made this possible.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: Prof. Solms has delved into the coplexity of the mind in an engaging and rational manner from both a scientific and philosophic angle. The MIND is indeed a mindboggling subject. Prof. Solms brings a rare clarity and understanding of the same in six engaging weeks. I enjoyed the course and wish to revisit the material many times to hone my understanding. I would GO FOR IT if offered again.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: Absolutely excellent. Dr Mark Solms is an interesting, engaging and enthusiastic presenter. There are some very interesting useful links, academic but still accessible to the average payperson. Would definitely recommend to anyone with an interest in this area.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: I've taken lots of Moocs now and this was right up there with the best. Mark has a passion for his subject that came across throughout, and he was genuinely interested in interacting with people taking the course. He built knowledge gradually but without ever dumbing down. I loved it.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: A really interesting course both for someone like me who knew very little, but also for those with experience in the field from whom I learned a lot from their comments - and sometimes their disagreements - generated by some of the course material. The course is excellently run and provides a good foundation for further study in the subject area.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: This course was highly informative, clear, concise, easily understood and very interesting. It provokes many questions and discussions with other learners, which enables you to see other people's views in order to expand on your own. The subject itself is exciting and worth learning about and the knowledge gained from it is very useful!

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: I really want to thank Mark Solms and the University of Capetown, because I could find this course very saolid and with a lot of extra-materials to go on reading after it is finished. title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: This course was fascinating - challengingly philosophical and scientific at times, but then you don't do a course like this to stay in your comfort zone. I spent about 3 hours a week on it, which when done in fragments seemed to go by fast. I particularly enjoyed the assignments, Mark Solms's videos, and the discussion postings.

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: What a fantastic course. Prof Solms is so engaging and he puts a very difficult subject across in terms us lay people can understand. I would recommend this course to everyone but with the caveat that you have to have time to listen carefully and think, it's not one to be rushed. I am sad it has ended! Thank you to all the team.

title: What Is a Mind?

title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: I found this course really useful because it gives learners -even with no prior knowledge of psychology, philosophy and neurosciences- a deep insights to what we consider mind with very good supporting materials and references. title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: I have done quite a few MOOCS in the last five years. This was one of the best. Professor Solms is a great communicator and scientist and master of his subject. title: What Is a Mind?
review_contents: This is a good interdisciplinary approach to the mind. title: What Is a Mind?

Professional Web Accessibility Auditing Made Easy
review_contents: Eye opening course that emphasizes why web accessibility is so important. Web authors and developers quickly learn the skills needed to identify and fix accessibility issues that may prevent some people from access content on the Web. Audit and write professional reports that guide clients on how to improve the accessibility of their websites.

title: Professional Web Accessibility Auditing Made Easy
review_contents: This is a very good corse for the introduction to web accessibility auditing. The course is well organized and the explanations are very clear for understanding basic concepts of web accesibility. It explains how to check accessibility on web sites using different tools.

title: Professional Web Accessibility Auditing Made Easy
review_contents: I found this course very enlightening. It helped me understand the concepts behind web accessibility and gave me some real tools to make sure our website is accessible. Fantastic course! hope it is repeated soon so I can get some colleagues to take it!!

title: Professional Web Accessibility Auditing Made Easy
review_contents: I went from knowing basically nothing about Web Accessibility to feeling capable of auditing Web pages. I now know what to look for, what tools to use, and how to make suggestions for improvements. This was a really helpful class!

title: Professional Web Accessibility Auditing Made Easy
review_contents:
This online course has met my expectation and delivered that is promissed: to develop skills and knowledge needed to make websites AODA compliance.

Thank you to Chang School of Continuing Education, Greg Gay and Igor Karasyov

Benoit

title: Professional Web Accessibility Auditing Made Easy

Behind the Scenes at the 21st Century Museum
review_contents: This course was an incredible mix of outstanding presenters, fascinating and relative topics, and educational videos. In addition, I found many practical take-aways that I noted for future use. The instructors really cared about increasing participants' knowledge level and in turn, that inspired participants to engage fully in the comment section of each lesson. Just an outstanding course!

title: Behind the Scenes at the 21st Century Museum
review_contents: The content is interesting and inspiring. The activist part of the museums is really highlighted, which is a role I'd never associated with museums. The course also makes you reflect on how culture and history is presented and preserved.

title: Behind the Scenes at the 21st Century Museum
review_contents: Fantastic 6 week course! A great introduction to some of the main themes and debates going on in the museum profession. Couldn't believe it was free!

title: Explore Animation
review_contents:
Good introduction to animation, but I wished there could have been a more systematic approach as to how the whole industry is run, or some best practices in the field.

Still, overall I would recommend this to anyone interested in animation.
